{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312042905286a19139f064623","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"id":"20260312042905286a19139f064623","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_7ee3476ea6cd49e68c4d5bc6","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Task List\n\n## Overview\n\n- **Feature**: F-006 Safety and Permission Guard\n- **Total Tasks**: 22\n- **Parallelizable**: 8 tasks marked with [P]\n- **User Stories**: US-1 ~ US-5\n\n---\n\n## Phase 0: Setup (T-001 ~ T-009)\n\n- [ ] [T-001] Create security module directory structure — file: src/security/\n  - Goal: Set up the security module folder structure\n  - Input: None\n  - Output: `src/security/` directory ready for implementation\n  - Acceptance: Directory exists, `.gitkeep` or placeholder file created\n  - Complexity: Low\n\n- [ ] [T-002] [P] Extend config.js with permission and audit settings — file: src/config.js\n  - Goal: Add configuration options for permissions and audit logging\n  - Input: Current config.js, spec.md Configuration Schema\n  - Output: Extended config with USER_PERMISSIONS parsing, AUDIT_LOG_DIR, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES\n  - Acceptance: Config exports permission-related settings, defaults match spec\n  - Complexity: Low\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Core Security (T-010 ~ T-039)\n\n### US-1: User Permission Levels\n\n- [ ] [T-010] [P] Implement PermissionService — file: src/security/permission.js\n  - Goal: Create permission service with level query and validation\n  - Input: I-1 PermissionService API, D-1 Permission Configuration\n  - Output: `permission.js` with `getUserPermission()`, `hasPermission()`, `getPermissionConfig()`\n  - Acceptance: AC-1.1 ~ AC-1.4 satisfied, permission levels correctly parsed from env\n  - Complexity: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-011] [P] Unit tests for PermissionService — file: tests/security/permission.test.js\n  - Goal: Comprehensive unit tests for permission service\n  - Input: T-010 implementation\n  - Output: Test file with permission parsing, level comparison, default behavior test cases\n  - Acceptance: Coverage > 90%, all edge cases tested\n  - Complexity: Medium\n\n### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n\n- [ ] [T-020] Implement PermissionMiddleware — file: src/security/permission-middleware.js\n  - Goal: Create middleware for command-level permission checking\n  - Input: I-2 PermissionMiddleware API, D-2 Command Metadata Extension\n  - Output: `permission-middleware.js` with `createPermissionMiddleware()`, `getRequiredPermission()`\n  - Acceptance: AC-2.1 ~ AC-2.5 satisfied, integrates with command router\n  - Complexity: Medium\n  - Depends on: T-010\n\n- [ ] [T-021] Integrate permission middleware into command router — file: src/bot/commands/index.js\n  - Goal: Wire permission middleware into the command routing flow\n  - Input: T-020 implementation, current command router\n  - Output: Modified `index.js` with middleware in the dispatch chain\n  - Acceptance: Permission check runs before command handler, denied commands return unified error\n  - Complexity: Low\n  - Depends on: T-020\n\n- [ ] [T-022] Update command registry with permission metadata — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  - Goal: Add `minPermission` and `requiresConfirmation` fields to command metadata\n  - Input: High-Risk Command Matrix from spec.md\n  - Output: Updated registry with permission requirements for stop, reset, retry, exec, force-unlock\n  - Acceptance: All high-risk commands have correct `minPermission` values\n  - Complexity: Low\n  - Depends on: T-020\n\n### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n\n- [ ] [T-030] [P] Implement ParameterSanitizer — file: src/security/sanitizer.js\n  - Goal: Create parameter sanitization utilities\n  - Input: I-3 ParameterSanitizer API\n  - Output: `sanitizer.js` with `sanitizePath()`, `sanitizeTargetId()`, `sanitizeGeneral()`, `hasDangerousPatterns()`\n  - Acceptance: AC-3.1 ~ AC-3.5 satisfied, dangerous patterns rejected\n  - Complexity: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-031] [P] Unit tests for ParameterSanitizer — file: tests/security/sanitizer.test.js\n  - Goal: Comprehensive unit tests for sanitizer\n  - Input: T-030 implementation\n  - Output: Test file with path traversal rejection, dangerous chars, valid inputs test cases\n  - Acceptance: Coverage > 90%, all dangerous patterns tested\n  - Complexity: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-032] Apply sanitizer to command handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n  - Goal: Integrate sanitizer into all command handlers that accept user input\n  - Input: T-030 implementation, existing command handlers\n  - Output: Modified handlers with parameter sanitization\n  - Acceptance: Path and targetId parameters sanitized before use, errors returned for invalid input\n  - Complexity: Low\n  - Depends on: T-030\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Confirmation Flow (T-100 ~ T-129)\n\n### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n\n- [ ] [T-100] Implement ConfirmationFlow — file: src/bot/commands/confirmation.js\n  - Goal: Create confirmation dialog handler with timeout management\n  - Input: I-4 ConfirmationFlow API, D-4 Pending Confirmation State\n  - Output: `confirmation.js` with `requestConfirmation()`, `hasPendingConfirmation()`, `cancelConfirmation()`, `handleConfirmationResponse()`\n  - Acceptance: AC-4.1 ~ AC-4.5 satisfied, 60-second timeout, CONFIRM text response\n  - Complexity: High\n\n- [ ] [T-101] Unit tests for ConfirmationFlow — file: tests/bot/confirmation.test.js\n  - Goal: Comprehensive unit tests for confirmation flow\n  - Input: T-100 implementation\n  - Output: Test file with Confirm/Cancel/Timeout flows, concurrent confirmations test cases\n  - Acceptance: Coverage > 90%, timeout behavior verified\n  - Complexity: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-102] Add confirmation to stop command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n  - Goal: Integrate confirmation flow for stop command\n  - Input: T-100 implementation, existing stop handler\n  - Output: Modified stop handler with confirmation dia