{"type":"user","uuid":"0f8ce7a1-34f3-4906-b37c-d3e95e33b3d8","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6d0a0f98ff49463b83557f73","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→import 'dotenv/config';\n   2→import { z } from 'zod';\n   3→\n   4→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n   5→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n   6→\n   7→const schema = z.object({\n   8→  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n   9→  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  10→  ALLOWED_USER_IDS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  11→  CODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\n  12→  CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n  13→  CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  14→  CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(15000),\n  15→  TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  16→  TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  17→  REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(120000),\n  18→  MAX_PROMPT_CHARS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8000),\n  19→  MAX_HISTORY_TURNS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  20→  WEB_HOST: z.string().default('127.0.0.1'),\n  21→  WEB_PORT: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8787),\n  22→  ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n  23→  ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  24→  SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n  25→  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['fatal', 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug', 'trace', 'silent']).default('info')\n  26→});\n  27→\n  28→const parsed = schema.parse(process.env);\n  29→\n  30→function parseAllowedUserIds(input) {\n  31→  return new Set(\n  32→    input\n  33→      .split(',')\n  34→      .map((id) => id.trim())\n  35→      .filter(Boolean)\n  36→  );\n  37→}\n  38→\n  39→function parseCsvList(input) {\n  40→  return input\n  41→    .split(',')\n  42→    .map((item) => item.trim())\n  43→    .filter(Boolean);\n  44→}\n  45→\n  46→function parseBoolean(input) {\n  47→  const normalized = (input ?? '').trim().toLowerCase();\n  48→  return normalized === '1' || normalized === 'true' || normalized === 'yes' || normalized === 'on';\n  49→}\n  50→\n  51→const enableTelegram = parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_TELEGRAM);\n  52→if (enableTelegram && !parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN) {\n  53→  throw new Error('ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true 时必须提供 TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN');\n  54→}\n  55→\n  56→const pipelineInfra = loadPipelineInfraConfig({\n  57→  env: process.env,\n  58→  argv: process.argv.slice(2),\n  59→  cwd: process.cwd()\n  60→});\n  61→\n  62→const daemonLogPaths = resolveDaemonLogPaths(pipelineInfra.projectRoot);\n  63→\n  64→export const config = Object.freeze({\n  65→  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n  66→  enableTelegram,\n  67→  allowedUserIds: parseAllowedUserIds(parsed.ALLOWED_USER_IDS),\n  68→  codebuddyBin: parsed.CODEBUDDY_BIN,\n  69→  codebuddyPermissionFlag: parsed.CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG,\n  70→  codebuddyEchoStdio: parseBoolean(parsed.CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO),\n  71→  codebuddyHeartbeatMs: parsed.CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS,\n  72→  telegramFileAllowedRoots: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS),\n  73→  telegramFileCandidateDirs: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS),\n  74→  requestTimeoutMs: parsed.REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS,\n  75→  maxPromptChars: parsed.MAX_PROMPT_CHARS,\n  76→  maxHistoryTurns: parsed.MAX_HISTORY_TURNS,\n  77→  webHost: parsed.WEB_HOST,\n  78→  webPort: parsed.WEB_PORT,\n  79→  enableSystemExec: parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC),\n  80→  allowedCommandPrefixes: parseCsvList(parsed.ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES),\n  81→  systemExecTimeoutMs: parsed.SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS,\n  82→  logLevel: parsed.LOG_LEVEL,\n  83→  pipelineInfra: Object.freeze({\n  84→    ...pipelineInfra,\n  85→    daemonLogPaths\n  86→  })\n  87→});\n  88→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde980818dd4e004028d576269ae9","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:31:10.361Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"ca5f2ee2-a347-4875-8a91-56e241755233","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde980818dd4e004028d576269ae9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed. Let me run the `prizmkit.analyze` cross-check:\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 `prizmkit.analyze` Report: F-006 Safety and Permission Guard\n\n**Input Files:**\n- `.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/spec.md`\n- `.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/plan.md`\n- `.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/tasks.md`\n\n**Analysis Channels:** 重复检测 | 歧义检测 | 不完整检测 | Prizm规则对齐 | 覆盖缺口 | 不一致性\n\n---\n\n### 🚨 CRITICAL Issues (2)\n\n| # | Level | Channel | Location | Issue | Fix Suggestion |\n|---|-------|---------|----------|-------|----------------|\n| **C1** | CRITICAL | 不一致性 | plan.md:85-88 vs spec.md:31-32 | **Command permission matrix mismatch** - `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` in plan shows `stop: 'operator'`, `reset: 'operator'`, but spec AC-2.2 explicitly requires `stop`/`reset`/`force-unlock` need `admin` permission | Update plan.md `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` to: `stop: 'admin'`, `reset: 'admin'`. Add `force-unlock: 'admin'` to the map |\n| **C2** | CRITICAL | 不完整检测 | tasks.md:134 | **T-104 references non-existent file** - Task says \"file: src/bot/commands/handlers/lock.js\" but verified this file does NOT exist in codebase. Existing handlers: bugfix.js, planner.js, plan.js, pipeline.js, stop.js, status.js, logs.js | Either: (a) Add T-000 to create lock.js handler first, or (b) Move force-unlock logic into pipeline.js handler |\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ HIGH Issues (4)\n\n| # | Level | Channel | Location | Issue | Fix Suggestion |\n|---|-------|---------|----------|-------|----------------|\n| **H1** | HIGH | 不一致性 | plan.md:48 vs spec.md:24 | **API function name mismatch** - spec AC-1.4 defines `getUserPermission(userId)` but plan.md C-1 exports `getUserRole(userId)`. Interface contract broken | Rename `getUserRole` to `getUserPermission` in plan.md to match spec |\n| **H2** | HIGH | 覆盖缺口 | plan.md | **`force-unlock` command not covered** - Listed in High-Risk Command Matrix (spec.md:94) but no component design or interface in plan.md for this command | Add C-5 component design for force-unlock or integrate into existing component |\n| **H3** | HIGH | 不一致性 | spec.md:100-104 vs plan.md:315-320 | **Config variable name mismatch** - Spec defines `AUDIT_LOG_DIR`, `AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB`, `AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES` but plan.md uses `AUDIT_LOG_PATH`, `AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS`. Also `USER_PERMISSIONS` default differs | Align plan.md I-2 config schema with spec.md Configuration section |\n| **H4** | HIGH | 覆盖缺口 | plan.md | **`--force` flag implementation missing** - Spec AC-4.4 requires `--force` flag to skip confirmation for admin users, but plan.md has no interface design for flag parsing in Confirmation Manager | Add `force` parameter handling in Confirmation Manager interface and integration example |\n\n---\n\n### 📝 MEDIUM Issues (5)\n\n| # | Level | Channel | Location | Issue | Fix Suggestion |\n|---|-------|---------|----------|-------|----------------|\n| **M1** | MEDIUM | 不一致性 | spec.md:44 vs plan.md:99-107 | **Sanitizer function naming mismatch** - Spec AC-3.4 defines `sanitizePath()` and `sanitizeTargetId()`, but plan.md C-2 exports `sanitizeParam()` and `validatePath()` | Align function names to spec or update spec |\n| **M2** | MEDIUM | 不完整检测 | plan.md:88 | **`HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS` set inconsistent** - plan shows `HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'retry', 'exec'])` but spec AC-2.1 includes `force-unlock` which is missing | Add `'force-unlock'` to the set |\n| **M3** | MEDIUM | 不一致性 | spec.md:90 vs plan.md:88 | **exec permission mismatch** - Spec matrix shows `exec` needs `admin`, but plan.md `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` shows `exec: 'operator'` | Align plan to spec: `exec: 'admin'` |\n| **M4** | MEDIUM | 覆盖缺口 | tasks.md | **Existing security module ignored** - Found existing `src/security/guard.js` and `src/security/system-guard.js` but plan.md proposes new `permission-guard.js`. Should integrate or extend existing code | Review existing security modules and plan integration strategy |\n| **M5** | MEDIUM | 不一致性 | plan.md:240-250 | **Log entry schema timestamp format invalid** - Shows `'2026-03-XX T10:30:00.000Z'` with placeholder 'XX' which is not valid ISO 8601 | Use actual example: `'2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z'` |\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Summary\n\n| Channel | CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW | Total |\n|---------|----------|------|--------|-----|-------|\n| 不一致性 | 1 | 3 | 2 | 0 | 6 |\n| 不完整检测 | 1 | 0 | 1 | 0 | 2 |\n| 覆盖缺口 | 0 | 2 | 1 | 0 | 3 |\n| 重复检测 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| 歧义检测 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| Prizm规则对齐 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| **Total** | **2** | **4** | **5** | **0** | **11** |\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Verdict: **NEEDS_FIXES**\n\n**Reason:** 2 CRITICAL issues found - command permission matrix mismatch and reference to non-existent file. These must be resolved before implementation can proceed.\n\n---\n\n## 📋 COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n```\nFROM: Reviewer Agent\nTO: Coordinator\nTYPE: COMPLETION_SIGNAL\nPHASE: 4 (Cross-check)\nFEATURE: F-006 Safety and Permission Guard\nVERDICT: NEEDS_FIXES\nCRITICAL_COUNT: 2\nHIGH_COUNT: 4\nACTION_REQUIRED: Return to PM for spec/plan/tasks alignment\n```\n\n**Recommended Actions for PM:**\n1. Fix C1: Align `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` in plan.md with spec.md AC-2.2 permission requirements\n2. Fix C2: Either create `lock.js` handler or move `force-unlock` to existing handler\n3. Address all HIGH issues for interface consistency\n\n[Agent ID: agent-9ab46f2f]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde980818dd4e004028d576269ae9","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:31:48.708Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
