{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312043200003076ff96144deb","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"id":"20260312043200003076ff96144deb","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde996dca1a8a7db84eb9206d2be9","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/tasks.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":11255,"output_tokens":162,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde99454ac3a78b6e02c647fa7407","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:32:03.550Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"8d6d7623-83d9-43d5-a76b-932bb78cee52","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde996a0933a0b3b9017574a1f5a0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→为 Telegram 管道控制增加安全护栏：用户权限分级、高风险命令授权校验、参数净化、敏感操作二次确认与审计日志。重点覆盖 stop/reset/retry/exec 等高风险指令，确保\"可用\"与\"可控\"并存。\n   6→\n   7→**Scope**: 权限分级模型、高风险命令拦截、参数净化、确认机制、审计日志。\n   8→\n   9→**Dependencies**: F-002 (Telegram Pipeline Command Router - completed), F-004 (Pipeline Process Controller - completed)\n  10→\n  11→---\n  12→\n  13→## User Stories\n  14→\n  15→### US-1: User Permission Levels\n  16→\n  17→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 基于用户 ID 的权限分级机制 **So that** 不同用户拥有不同的操作权限\n  18→\n  19→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  20→- AC-1.1: 支持三级权限: `admin` | `operator` | `viewer`\n  21→- AC-1.2: 通过环境变量 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 配置用户权限映射\n  22→- AC-1.3: 未配置时所有授权用户默认为 `operator`\n  23→- AC-1.4: 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` API 查询用户权限级别\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 高风险命令需要特定权限级别才能执行 **So that** 敏感操作不会被未授权用户触发\n  28→\n  29→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  30→- AC-2.1: 定义高风险命令列表: `stop`, `reset`, `retry`, `exec`, `force-unlock`\n  31→- AC-2.2: `stop`/`reset`/`force-unlock` 需要 `admin` 权限\n  32→- AC-2.3: `retry` 需要 `operator` 权限\n  33→- AC-2.4: `exec` 需要 `admin` 权限且受 `ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC` 控制\n  34→- AC-2.5: 权限不足时返回统一拒绝消息，不暴露敏感信息\n  35→\n  36→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n  37→\n  38→**As a** 系统 **I want** 所有命令参数经过净化与规则校验 **So that** 非法路径与危险参数组合被拒绝\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  41→- AC-3.1: 路径参数禁止 `..`、绝对路径穿越、shell 元字符\n  42→- AC-3.2: targetId 参数仅允许 `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+` 格式\n  43→- AC-3.3: 拒绝包含 `; | & $ \\` ' \" ( ) < >` 等危险字符的参数\n  44→- AC-3.4: 提供 `sanitizePath()` 和 `sanitizeTargetId()` 工具函数\n  45→\n  46→### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n  47→\n  48→**As a** 用户 **I want** 高风险命令执行前需要明确确认 **So that** 误操作可以被及时阻止\n  49→\n  50→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  51→- AC-4.1: `stop`、`reset`、`force-unlock` 需要二次确认\n  52→- AC-4.2: 确认消息包含操作摘要和风险提示\n  53→- AC-4.3: 用户需在 60 秒内回复确认，否则操作取消\n  54→- AC-4.4: 支持 `--force` 标志跳过确认（仅限 `admin` 用户）\n  55→\n  56→### US-5: Audit Logging\n  57→\n  58→**As a** 运维人员 **I want** 每次敏感操作都写入审计日志 **So that** 我可以追溯操作历史\n  59→\n  60→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  61→- AC-5.1: 审计日志记录: timestamp, userId, username, action, params, result\n  62→- AC-5.2: 日志存储于 `logs/audit.log`（JSON Lines 格式）\n  63→- AC-5.3: 提供按会话 ID 或用户 ID 检索审计记录的 API\n  64→- AC-5.4: 日志轮转: 单文件最大 10MB，保留最近 5 个文件\n  65→\n  66→---\n  67→\n  68→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  69→\n  70→- **NFR-1 Performance**: 权限检查 < 5ms，参数净化 < 2ms，审计日志异步写入\n  71→- **NFR-2 Reliability**: 审计日志写入失败不影响命令执行，确认超时无死锁\n  72→- **NFR-3 Maintainability**: 权限配置与代码分离，高风险命令列表可配置，测试覆盖率 > 90%\n  73→- **NFR-4 Security**: 不在错误消息中暴露内部路径或配置，审计日志不可被普通用户访问\n  74→\n  75→---\n  76→\n  77→## Scope Boundaries\n  78→\n  79→**In Scope**: 用户权限分级模型与配置、高风险命令授权检查中间件、参数净化工具函数、确认对话机制、审计日志服务\n  80→\n  81→**Out of Scope**: 用户认证（已有 `isAllowedUser`）、Web UI 权限管理、数据库存储、加密存储\n  82→\n  83→---\n  84→\n  85→## High-Risk Command Matrix\n  86→\n  87→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation | Notes |\n  88→|---------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n  89→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 停止运行中管道 |\n  90→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 重置管道状态 |\n  91→| `retry` | operator | No | 重试失败目标 |\n  92→| `exec` | admin | No | 执行系统命令 |\n  93→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 强制释放锁 |\n  94→\n  95→---\n  96→\n  97→## Configuration\n  98→\n  99→```env\n 100→USER_PERMISSIONS=123456789:admin,987654321:operator\n 101→AUDIT_LOG_DIR=logs\n 102→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB=10\n 103→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES=5\n 104→```\n 105→\n 106→---\n 107→\n 108→## Decisions\n 109→\n 110→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 111→|----|------|----------|\n 112→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用三级权限模型（admin/operator/viewer）|\n 113→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 确认机制使用文字确认（\"CONFIRM\"），不依赖 inline keyboard |\n 114→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 审计日志使用 JSON Lines 格式 |\n 115→| D4 | 2026-03-12 | `--force` 标志仅限 admin 用户 |\n 116→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde99454ac3a78b6e02c647fa7407","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:32:03.558Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"c5613ec5-f0b7-4c32-b845-ff706454afd9","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde996be8de9e2b7fa8acf3e130c1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Technical Implementation Plan\n   2→\n   3→## Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   7→│                     Telegram Bot Layer                          │\n   8→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n   9→│  │                   Command Handlers                       │   │\n  10→│  │   (stop.js, pipeline.js, bugfix.js, status.js, ...)    │   │\n  11→│  └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  12→│                        │                                        │\n  13→│                        ▼                                        │\n  14→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  15→│  │              Security Guard Layer (NEW)                  │   │\n  16→│  │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐    │   │\n  17→│  │  │ Permission  │ │   Param     │ │  Confirmation   │    │   │\n  18→│  │  │   Guard     │ │ Sanitizer   │ │    Manager      │    │   │\n  19→│  │  └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────────┘    │   │\n  20→│  └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  21→│                        │                                        │\n  22→│                        ▼                                        │\n  23→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  24→│  │              Pipeline Controller (F-004)                 │   │\n  25→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  26→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  27→│\n  28→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  29→│  │              Audit Log Service (NEW)                     │\n  30→│  │                   (Async Writing)                        │\n  31→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  32→```\n  33→\n  34→---\n  35→\n  36→## Component Design\n  37→\n  38→### C-1: Permission Guard (`src/security/permission-guard.js`)\n  39→\n  40→**Purpose**: 用户权限分级与命令授权校验\n  41→\n  42→**Interface**:\n  43→```javascript\n  44→/**\n  45→ * Get user permission level\n  46→ * @param {string|number} userId - Telegram user ID\n  47→ * @returns {'admin'|'operator'|'viewer'}\n  48→ */\n  49→export function getUserRole(userId);\n  50→\n  51→/**\n  52→ * Check if user can execute command\n  53→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  54→ * @param {string} command - Command name\n  55→ * @returns {{ allowed: boolean, requiresConfirmation: boolean, reason?: string }}\n  56→ */\n  57→export function checkCommandPermission(userId, command);\n  58→\n  59→/**\n  60→ * Check if user is admin\n  61→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  62→ * @returns {boolean}\n  63→ */\n  64→export function isAdmin(userId);\n  65→```\n  66→\n  67→**Data Model**:\n  68→```javascript\n  69→// Config from env: USER_PERMISSIONS=123:admin,456:operator\n  70→const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n  71→  viewer: 0,\n  72→  operator: 1,\n  73→  admin: 2\n  74→};\n  75→\n  76→const COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  77→  status: 'viewer',\n  78→  logs: 'viewer',\n  79→  pipeline: 'operator',\n  80→  bugfix: 'operator',\n  81→  planner: 'operator',\n  82→  stop: 'operator',\n  83→  reset: 'operator',\n  84→  retry: 'operator',\n  85→  exec: 'operator'\n  86→};\n  87→\n  88→const HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'retry', 'exec']);\n  89→```\n  90→\n  91→---\n  92→\n  93→### C-2: Param Sanitizer (`src/security/param-sanitizer.js`)\n  94→\n  95→**Purpose**: 参数净化与危险模式检测\n  96→\n  97→**Interface**:\n  98→```javascript\n  99→/**\n 100→ * Sanitize string parameter\n 101→ * @param {string} input - Raw input\n 102→ * @param {Object} options\n 103→ * @param {number} [options.maxLength=200]\n 104→ * @param {boolean} [options.isPath=false]\n 105→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, value?: string, error?: string }}\n 106→ */\n 107→export function sanitizeParam(input, options);\n 108→\n 109→/**\n 110→ * Validate path parameter\n 111→ * @param {string} path - Path to validate\n 112→ * @param {string[]} allowedRoots - Allowed root directories\n 113→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, resolved?: string, error?: string }}\n 114→ */\n 115→export function validatePath(path, allowedRoots);\n 116→\n 117→/**\n 118→ * Check for dangerous patterns\n 119→ * @param {string} input\n 120→ * @returns {{ safe: boolean, patterns: string[] }}\n 121→ */\n 122→export function detectDangerousPatterns(input);\n 123→```\n 124→\n 125→**Dangerous Patterns**:\n 126→```javascript\n 127→const DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [\n 128→  /\\.\\./,           // Path traversal\n 129→  /[`$]/,           // Shell injection\n 130→  /~/,              // Home directory\n 131→  /\\$\\(/,           // Command substitution\n 132→  /\\|\\|/,           // Command chain\n 133→  /&&/,             // Command chain\n 134→  /;.*$/,           // Command separator\n 135→  /--exec\\b/,       // Exec flag\n 136→  /--eval\\b/,       // Eval flag\n 137→];\n 138→```\n 139→\n 140→---\n 141→\n 142→### C-3: Confirmation Manager (`src/security/confirmation-manager.js`)\n 143→\n 144→**Purpose**: 高风险操作二次确认流程\n 145→\n 146→**Interface**:\n 147→```javascript\n 148→/**\n 149→ * Create pending confirmation\n 150→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 151→ * @param {string} action - Action name\n 152→ * @param {Object} params - Action parameters\n 153→ * @param {number} [timeoutMs=60000]\n 154→ * @returns {{ confirmId: string, message: string }}\n 155→ */\n 156→export function createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs);\n 157→\n 158→/**\n 159→ * Check confirmation status\n 160→ * @param {string confirmId\n 161→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 162→ * @returns {{ status: 'pending'|'confirmed'|'expired'|'not_found', action?: string, params?: Object }}\n 163→ */\n 164→export function checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId);\n 165→\n 166→/**\n 167→ * Confirm pending action\n 168→ * @param {string} confirmId\n 169→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 170→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, action?: string, params?: Object, error?: string }}\n 171→ */\n 172→export function confirmAction(confirmId, userId);\n 173→\n 174→/**\n 175→ * Cancel pending confirmation\n 176→ * @param {string} confirmId\n 177→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 178→ */\n 179→export function cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId);\n 180→```\n 181→\n 182→**Data Model**:\n 183→```javascript\n 184→// Stored in memory with Map\n 185→const pendingConfirmations = new Map();\n 186→\n 187→// Structure:\n 188→{\n 189→  confirmId: 'uuid-v4',\n 190→  userId: 123456789,\n 191→  action: 'stop',\n 192→  params: { type: 'feature' },\n 193→  createdAt: Date.now(),\n 194→  expiresAt: Date.now() + 60000\n 195→}\n 196→```\n 197→\n 198→---\n 199→\n 200→### C-4: Audit Log Service (`src/services/audit-log-service.js`)\n 201→\n 202→**Purpose**: 敏感操作审计日志\n 203→\n 204→**Interface**:\n 205→```javascript\n 206→/**\n 207→ * Initialize audit log service\n 208→ * @param {Object} config\n 209→ * @param {string} config.logPath - Log directory path\n 210→ * @param {number} config.retentionDays - Days to keep logs\n 211→ */\n 212→export function initAuditLogService(config);\n 213→\n 214→/**\n 215→ * Log sensitive action\n 216→ * @param {Object} entry\n 217→ * @param {string|number} entry.userId\n 218→ * @param {string} entry.action\n 219→ * @param {Object} entry.params\n 220→ * @param {string} entry.result - 'success'|'denied'|'failed'\n 221→ * @param {string} [entry.reason]\n 222→ * @returns {Promise<void>}\n 223→ */\n 224→export function logAuditEntry(entry);\n 225→\n 226→/**\n 227→ * Query audit logs\n 228→ * @param {Object} filters\n 229→ * @param {string|number} [filters.userId]\n 230→ * @param {string} [filters.action]\n 231→ * @param {Date} [filters.startDate]\n 232→ * @param {Date} [filters.endDate]\n 233→ * @param {number} [filters.limit=100]\n 234→ * @returns {Promise<Object[]>}\n 235→ */\n 236→export function queryAuditLogs(filters);\n 237→```\n 238→\n 239→**Log Entry Schema**:\n 240→```javascript\n 241→{\n 242→  timestamp: '2026-03-XX T10:30:00.000Z',\n 243→  userId: '123456789',\n 244→  role: 'operator',\n 245→  action: 'stop',\n 246→  params: { type: 'feature' },\n 247→  result: 'success',\n 248→  reason: null,\n 249→  sessionId: 'telegram-123456789'\n 250→}\n 251→```\n 252→\n 253→**File Format**: JSON Lines (`.jsonl`)\n 254→```\n 255→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-XX T10:30:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"123456789\",...}\n 256→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-XX T10:31:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"987654321\",...}\n 257→```\n 258→\n 259→---\n 260→\n 261→## Integration Points\n 262→\n 263→### I-1: Command Handler Integration\n 264→\n 265→**Before (stop.js)**:\n 266→```javascript\n 267→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 268→  const { params, reply } = handlerCtx;\n 269→  const result = await stopPipeline({ type: pipelineType });\n 270→  // ...\n 271→}\n 272→```\n 273→\n 274→**After (stop.js)**:\n 275→```javascript\n 276→import { checkCommandPermission, getUserRole } from '../../security/permission-guard.js';\n 277→import { createConfirmation, checkConfirmation } from '../../security/confirmation-manager.js';\n 278→import { sanitizeParam } from '../../security/param-sanitizer.js';\n 279→import { logAuditEntry } from '../../services/audit-log-service.js';\n 280→\n 281→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 282→  const { params, reply, userId, session } = handlerCtx;\n 283→  \n 284→  // 1. Permission check\n 285→  const perm = checkCommandPermission(userId, 'stop');\n 286→  if (!perm.allowed) {\n 287→    await logAuditEntry({ userId, action: 'stop', params, result: 'denied', reason: perm.reason });\n 288→    await reply('⛔ 权限不足');\n 289→    return;\n 290→  }\n 291→  \n 292→  // 2. Parameter sanitization\n 293→  const type = sanitizeParam(params.type || 'feature', { maxLength: 50 });\n 294→  if (!type.ok) {\n 295→    await reply(`❌ 参数无效: ${type.error}`);\n 296→    return;\n 297→  }\n 298→  \n 299→  // 3. Confirmation (if required)\n 300→  if (perm.requiresConfirmation) {\n 301→    const confirm = await handleConfirmation(handlerCtx, 'stop', { type: type.value });\n 302→    if (!confirm.confirmed) return;\n 303→  }\n 304→  \n 305→  // 4. Execute\n 306→  const result = await stopPipeline({ type: type.value });\n 307→  await logAuditEntry({ userId, action: 'stop', params, result: result.ok ? 'success' : 'failed' });\n 308→  // ...\n 309→}\n 310→```\n 311→\n 312→### I-2: Config Extension (`src/config.js`)\n 313→\n 314→```javascript\n 315→// Add to schema\n 316→USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 317→ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 318→AUDIT_LOG_PATH: z.string().optional().default('./logs/audit'),\n 319→AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(30),\n 320→\n 321→// Add to config export\n 322→userPermissions: parseUserPermissions(parsed.USER_PERMISSIONS),\n 323→allowAdminSkipConfirm: parseBoolean(parsed.ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM),\n 324→auditLogPath: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_PATH,\n 325→auditRetentionDays: parsed.AUDIT_RETENTION_DAYS,\n 326→```\n 327→\n 328→---\n 329→\n 330→## Test Strategy\n 331→\n 332→### Unit Tests\n 333→\n 334→| Module | Test Cases |\n 335→|--------|------------|\n 336→| permission-guard | Role hierarchy, permission matrix, default viewer |\n 337→| param-sanitizer | Dangerous patterns, path validation, length limits |\n 338→| confirmation-manager | Create/confirm/expire/cancel flows |\n 339→| audit-log-service | Write, query, rotation |\n 340→\n 341→### Integration Tests\n 342→\n 343→| Scenario | Validation |\n 344→|----------|------------|\n 345→| Operator stop flow | Permission → Confirm → Execute → Log |\n 346→| Viewer denied | Returns denied message, logs denial |\n 347→| Dangerous param rejected | Shell injection blocked |\n 348→| Audit query by user | Returns correct entries |\n 349→\n 350→---\n 351→\n 352→## Risks & Mitigations\n 353→\n 354→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 355→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 356→| Confirmation timeout during network issues | Medium | Low | Allow re-initiation, log timeout |\n 357→| Audit log disk full | Low | Medium | Rotation + size limit + async write |\n 358→| Permission config error | Medium | High | Default to most restrictive, validate on startup |\n 359→\n 360→---\n 361→\n 362→## File Changes Summary\n 363→\n 364→| File | Action | Purpose |\n 365→|------|--------|---------|\n 366→| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | NEW | Permission tiers & command auth |\n 367→| `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` | NEW | Parameter sanitization |\n 368→| `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` | NEW | Confirmation flow |\n 369→| `src/services/audit-log-service.js` | NEW | Audit logging |\n 370→| `src/config.js` | MODIFY | Add security config |\n 371→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 372→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 373→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 374→| `src/security/index.js` | NEW | Security module exports |\n 375→| `tests/security/*.test.js` | NEW | Unit tests |\n 376→| `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js` | NEW | Integration tests |\n 377→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde99454ac3a78b6e02c647fa7407","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:32:03.559Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"57929509-1f33-4409-bf2b-7e13e8d60bb1","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde996dca1a8a7db84eb9206d2be9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Task Breakdown\n   2→\n   3→## Phase 1: Setup (T-001 ~ T-009)\n   4→\n   5→- [ ] [T-001] [P] Create `src/security/index.js` module exports — file: src/security/index.js\n   6→- [ ] [T-002] [P] Extend `src/config.js` with security configuration — file: src/config.js\n   7→- [ ] [T-003] [P] Update `.env.example` with new security env vars — file: .env.example\n   8→\n   9→---\n  10→\n  11→## Phase 2: Foundational (T-010 ~ T-099)\n  12→\n  13→### Permission Guard Module\n  14→\n  15→- [ ] [T-010] [P] Implement `permission-guard.js` core logic — file: src/security/permission-guard.js\n  16→  - Goal: Implement role hierarchy and permission checking\n  17→  - Input: userId, command name\n  18→  - Output: { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  19→  - Acceptance: All role/command combinations tested\n  20→  - Complexity: Medium\n  21→\n  22→- [ ] [T-011] Implement `permission-guard.js` unit tests — file: tests/security/permission-guard.test.js\n  23→  - Goal: Verify permission matrix behavior\n  24→  - Input: Mock users with different roles\n  25→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  26→  - Acceptance: All edge cases covered (unknown user, invalid command)\n  27→  - Complexity: Low\n  28→  - Depends: T-010\n  29→\n  30→### Param Sanitizer Module\n  31→\n  32→- [ ] [T-012] [P] Implement `param-sanitizer.js` core logic — file: src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n  33→  - Goal: Sanitize parameters and detect dangerous patterns\n  34→  - Input: Raw string parameters\n  35→  - Output: { ok, value?, error? }\n  36→  - Acceptance: All dangerous patterns detected\n  37→  - Complexity: Medium\n  38→\n  39→- [ ] [T-013] Implement `param-sanitizer.js` unit tests — file: tests/security/param-sanitizer.test.js\n  40→  - Goal: Verify sanitization behavior\n  41→  - Input: Various dangerous and safe inputs\n  42→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  43→  - Acceptance: Path traversal, shell injection, length limits tested\n  44→  - Complexity: Low\n  45→  - Depends: T-012\n  46→\n  47→### Confirmation Manager Module\n  48→\n  49→- [ ] [T-014] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` core logic — file: src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n  50→  - Goal: Manage confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  51→  - Input: userId, action, params, timeout\n  52→  - Output: confirmId, status, action confirmation\n  53→  - Acceptance: Create/confirm/expire/cancel flows work\n  54→  - Complexity: Medium\n  55→\n  56→- [ ] [T-015] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` unit tests — file: tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js\n  57→  - Goal: Verify confirmation lifecycle\n  58→  - Input: Various confirmation scenarios\n  59→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  60→  - Acceptance: Timeout, cancel, double-confirm tested\n  61→  - Complexity: Low\n  62→  - Depends: T-014\n  63→\n  64→### Audit Log Service\n  65→\n  66→- [ ] [T-016] Implement `audit-log-service.js` core logic — file: src/services/audit-log-service.js\n  67→  - Goal: Write and query audit logs\n  68→  - Input: Audit entries, query filters\n  69→  - Output: JSON Lines log files\n  70→  - Acceptance: Async write, query by user/time/action\n  71→  - Complexity: Medium\n  72→\n  73→- [ ] [T-017] Implement `audit-log-service.js` unit tests — file: tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js\n  74→  - Goal: Verify logging behavior\n  75→  - Input: Log entries, query parameters\n  76→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  77→  - Acceptance: Write, query, rotation tested\n  78→  - Complexity: Low\n  79→  - Depends: T-016\n  80→\n  81→---\n  82→\n  83→## Phase 3: User Stories (T-100+)\n  84→\n  85→### US-1: Permission Tiers\n  86→\n  87→- [ ] [T-101] [US-1] Integrate permission guard into command registry — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  88→  - Goal: Add permission che