{"type":"user","uuid":"e3113024-666c-4e4b-b251-14fe1936ee8f","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_160a531a00c24556965a7249","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-dev\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated module implementer (multi-instance). Follows prizmkit.implement workflow with TDD, marks tasks [x] in tasks.md, works within assigned Git worktrees. Use when implementing specific feature modules.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-implement, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Dev Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的模块实现者。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"建筑工人\"——严格按图纸施工，使用 PrizmKit 的 implement 工作流作为执行引擎，专注于：\n  14→- 按照 tasks.md 和 plan.md 中的接口设计逐任务实现功能模块\n  15→- 遵循 TDD 方式开发（测试先行）\n  16→- 完成后立即标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`\n  17→- 产出代码和单元测试\n  18→\n  19→### 项目上下文\n  20→\n  21→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。实现前先读 `root.prizm` 了解规则和已知陷阱（TRAPS），修改某模块时读该模块的文档。\n  22→\n  23→### 制品路径\n  24→\n  25→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  26→|------|------|\n  27→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  28→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  29→\n  30→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  31→\n  32→1. 按照分配的任务和 plan.md 中的接口设计实现功能模块\n  33→2. 遵循 TDD 方式：先写测试，再实现，再验证\n  34→3. 产出的代码必须通过本模块的单元测试\n  35→4. 发现接口设计歧义时，立即通过 Coordinator 上报 PM（不自行假设）\n  36→5. 遵循 `prizmkit.implement` 工作流：读取 tasks.md + plan.md + spec.md，逐任务实现\n  37→6. 每个任务完成后**立即**标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`（不批量标记）\n  38→7. 实现前读取 `.prizm-docs/` TRAPS 段避免已知陷阱\n  39→8. 检查点任务须验证构建通过和测试通过后才能继续下一阶段\n  40→9. 顺序任务按序执行，失败则停止；并行 `[P]` 任务可继续\n  41→10. 新建子模块时，生成对应的 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  42→\n  43→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  44→\n  45→- 不修改 plan.md 中的接口设计（修改需通过 PM）\n  46→- 不修改其他 Dev Agent 负责的模块代码\n  47→- 不进行集成测试（Reviewer 的职责）\n  48→- 不直接运行 git commit（由 Coordinator 通过 prizmkit.committer 统一提交）\n  49→- 不修改 `.prizmkit/specs/` 中除 `tasks.md`（标记 [x]）以外的任何文件\n  50→- 不为 bug 修复创建新的文档条目；bug 修复是现有功能的完善，应更新原始功能的文档而非在 REGISTRY.md 中创建新条目\n  51→\n  52→### 行为规则\n  53→\n  54→```\n  55→DEV-01: 实现必须严格符合 plan.md 中定义的接口设计\n  56→DEV-02: 每个公开 API/函数必须有对应的单元测试\n  57→DEV-03: 发现接口设计歧义时，不得自行假设，必须上报\n  58→DEV-04: 任务完成后必须运行全部本模块测试\n  59→DEV-05: 代码提交信息遵循 Conventional Commits 格式\n  60→DEV-06: 不得引入未在任务描述中声明的外部依赖\n  61→DEV-07: 遵循 prizmkit.implement 工作流\n  62→DEV-08: 每个任务完成后立即标记 tasks.md [x]\n  63→DEV-09: TDD：先写测试 → 再实现 → 再验证\n  64→DEV-10: 实现每个模块前必须读取 .prizm-docs/ TRAPS 段\n  65→DEV-11: 检查点任务必须验证构建通过和测试通过\n  66→DEV-12: 新建子模块时生成 L2 .prizm-docs/ 文档\n  67→```\n  68→\n  69→### 工作流程\n  70→\n  71→1. 接收任务分配\n  72→2. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` 和相关模块文档\n  73→3. 读取 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` 中的 `tasks.md`、`plan.md`、`spec.md`\n  74→4. 对每个分配的任务，按 tasks.md 顺序执行：\n  75→   a. 读取目标文件模块的文档（检查 TRAPS 和 DECISIONS）\n  76→   b. TDD：基于验收标准编写测试 → 实现功能代码 → 运行测试验证\n  77→   c. 在 tasks.md 中标记该任务为 `[x]`\n  78→   d. 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 给 Coordinator\n  79→5. 如遇检查点任务，验证构建通过和测试通过后才继续\n  80→6. 遇到接口设计歧义，发送 ESCALATION（不自行假设）\n  81→7. 如新建了子模块，生成对应 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  82→8. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n  83→\n  84→### 异常处理\n  85→\n  86→| 场景 | 策略 |\n  87→|------|------|\n  88→| 接口设计歧义 | 标记 BLOCKED → ESCALATION → 等待 PM 裁定 |\n  89→| 单元测试失败 | 最多重试修复 3 次 → 仍失败则 ISSUE_REPORT |\n  90→| 外部依赖不可用 | 使用 Mock → 标注说明 |\n  91→| 任务超出预估 | ESCALATION → 建议 PM 拆分任务 |\n  92→\n  93→### 通信规则\n  94→\n  95→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n  96→- 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 汇报每个子任务完成\n  97→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 标志所有任务完成\n  98→- 发送 ESCALATION 上报接口歧义或任务阻塞\n  99→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 100→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde9b972165b5f35eeda38e0e2170","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:34:39.856Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"bb2e10b2-9e76-4e17-86bf-bcb0ef8631c9","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_910f412c6bbb4930a5182b44","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Technical Implementation Plan\n   2→\n   3→## Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   7→│                     Telegram Bot Layer                          │\n   8→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n   9→│  │                   Command Handlers                       │   │\n  10→│  │   (stop.js, pipeline.js, bugfix.js, status.js, ...)    │   │\n  11→│  └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  12→│                        │                                        │\n  13→│                        ▼                                        │\n  14→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  15→│  │              Security Guard Layer (NEW)                  │   │\n  16→│  │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐    │   │\n  17→│  │  │ Permission  │ │   Param     │ │  Confirmation   │    │   │\n  18→│  │  │   Guard     │ │ Sanitizer   │ │    Manager      │    │   │\n  19→│  │  └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────────┘    │   │\n  20→│  └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  21→│                        │                                        │\n  22→│                        ▼                                        │\n  23→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  24→│  │              Pipeline Controller (F-004)                 │   │\n  25→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  26→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  27→│\n  28→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  29→│  │              Audit Log Service (NEW)                     │\n  30→│  │                   (Async Writing)                        │\n  31→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  32→```\n  33→\n  34→---\n  35→\n  36→## Component Design\n  37→\n  38→### C-1: Permission Guard (`src/security/permission-guard.js`)\n  39→\n  40→**Purpose**: 用户权限分级与命令授权校验\n  41→\n  42→**Interface**:\n  43→```javascript\n  44→/**\n  45→ * Get user permission level\n  46→ * @param {string|number} userId - Telegram user ID\n  47→ * @returns {'admin'|'operator'|'viewer'}\n  48→ */\n  49→export function getUserRole(userId);\n  50→\n  51→/**\n  52→ * Check if user can execute command\n  53→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  54→ * @param {string} command - Command name\n  55→ * @returns {{ allowed: boolean, requiresConfirmation: boolean, reason?: string }}\n  56→ */\n  57→export function checkCommandPermission(userId, command);\n  58→\n  59→/**\n  60→ * Check if user is admin\n  61→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  62→ * @returns {boolean}\n  63→ */\n  64→export function isAdmin(userId);\n  65→```\n  66→\n  67→**Data Model**:\n  68→```javascript\n  69→// Config from env: USER_PERMISSIONS=123:admin,456:operator\n  70→const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n  71→  viewer: 0,\n  72→  operator: 1,\n  73→  admin: 2\n  74→};\n  75→\n  76→const COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  77→  status: 'viewer',\n  78→  logs: 'viewer',\n  79→  pipeline: 'operator',\n  80→  bugfix: 'operator',\n  81→  planner: 'operator',\n  82→  stop: 'admin',\n  83→  reset: 'admin',\n  84→  retry: 'operator',\n  85→  exec: 'admin',\n  86→  'force-unlock': 'admin'\n  87→};\n  88→\n  89→const HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'retry', 'exec', 'force-unlock']);\n  90→```\n  91→\n  92→---\n  93→\n  94→### C-2: Param Sanitizer (`src/security/param-sanitizer.js`)\n  95→\n  96→**Purpose**: 参数净化与危险模式检测\n  97→\n  98→**Interface**:\n  99→```javascript\n 100→/**\n 101→ * Sanitize string parameter\n 102→ * @param {string} input - Raw input\n 103→ * @param {Object} options\n 104→ * @param {number} [options.maxLength=200]\n 105→ * @param {boolean} [options.isPath=false]\n 106→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, value?: string, error?: string }}\n 107→ */\n 108→export function sanitizeParam(input, options);\n 109→\n 110→/**\n 111→ * Validate path parameter\n 112→ * @param {string} path - Path to validate\n 113→ * @param {string[]} allowedRoots - Allowed root directories\n 114→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, resolved?: string, error?: string }}\n 115→ */\n 116→export function validatePath(path, allowedRoots);\n 117→\n 118→/**\n 119→ * Check for dangerous patterns\n 120→ * @param {string} input\n 121→ * @returns {{ safe: boolean, patterns: string[] }}\n 122→ */\n 123→export function detectDangerousPatterns(input);\n 124→```\n 125→\n 126→**Dangerous Patterns**:\n 127→```javascript\n 128→const DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [\n 129→  /\\.\\./,           // Path traversal\n 130→  /[`$]/,           // Shell injection\n 131→  /~/,              // Home directory\n 132→  /\\$\\(/,           // Command substitution\n 133→  /\\|\\|/,           // Command chain\n 134→  /&&/,             // Command chain\n 135→  /;.*$/,           // Command separator\n 136→  /--exec\\b/,       // Exec flag\n 137→  /--eval\\b/,       // Eval flag\n 138→];\n 139→```\n 140→\n 141→---\n 142→\n 143→### C-3: Confirmation Manager (`src/security/confirmation-manager.js`)\n 144→\n 145→**Purpose**: 高风险操作二次确认流程\n 146→\n 147→**Interface**:\n 148→```javascript\n 149→/**\n 150→ * Create pending confirmation\n 151→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 152→ * @param {string} action - Action name\n 153→ * @param {Object} params - Action parameters\n 154→ * @param {number} [timeoutMs=60000]\n 155→ * @returns {{ confirmId: string, message: string }}\n 156→ */\n 157→export function createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs);\n 158→\n 159→/**\n 160→ * Check confirmation status\n 161→ * @param {string confirmId\n 162→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 163→ * @returns {{ status: 'pending'|'confirmed'|'expired'|'not_found', action?: string, params?: Object }}\n 164→ */\n 165→export function checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId);\n 166→\n 167→/**\n 168→ * Confirm pending action\n 169→ * @param {string} confirmId\n 170→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 171→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, action?: string, params?: Object, error?: string }}\n 172→ */\n 173→export function confirmAction(confirmId, userId);\n 174→\n 175→/**\n 176→ * Cancel pending confirmation\n 177→ * @param {string} confirmId\n 178→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 179→ */\n 180→export function cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId);\n 181→```\n 182→\n 183→**Data Model**:\n 184→```javascript\n 185→// Stored in memory with Map\n 186→const pendingConfirmations = new Map();\n 187→\n 188→// Structure:\n 189→{\n 190→  confirmId: 'uuid-v4',\n 191→  userId: 123456789,\n 192→  action: 'stop',\n 193→  params: { type: 'feature' },\n 194→  createdAt: Date.now(),\n 195→  expiresAt: Date.now() + 60000\n 196→}\n 197→```\n 198→\n 199→---\n 200→\n 201→### C-4: Audit Log Service (`src/services/audit-log-service.js`)\n 202→\n 203→**Purpose**: 敏感操作审计日志\n 204→\n 205→**Interface**:\n 206→```javascript\n 207→/**\n 208→ * Initialize audit log service\n 209→ * @param {Object} config\n 210→ * @param {string} config.logPath - Log directory path\n 211→ * @param {number} config.retentionDays - Days to keep logs\n 212→ */\n 213→export function initAuditLogService(config);\n 214→\n 215→/**\n 216→ * Log sensitive action\n 217→ * @param {Object} entry\n 218→ * @param {string|number} entry.userId\n 219→ * @param {string} entry.action\n 220→ * @param {Object} entry.params\n 221→ * @param {string} entry.result - 'success'|'denied'|'failed'\n 222→ * @param {string} [entry.reason]\n 223→ * @returns {Promise<void>}\n 224→ */\n 225→export function logAuditEntry(entry);\n 226→\n 227→/**\n 228→ * Query audit logs\n 229→ * @param {Object} filters\n 230→ * @param {string|number} [filters.userId]\n 231→ * @param {string} [filters.action]\n 232→ * @param {Date} [filters.startDate]\n 233→ * @param {Date} [filters.endDate]\n 234→ * @param {number} [filters.limit=100]\n 235→ * @returns {Promise<Object[]>}\n 236→ */\n 237→export function queryAuditLogs(filters);\n 238→```\n 239→\n 240→**Log Entry Schema**:\n 241→```javascript\n 242→{\n 243→  timestamp: '2026-03-XX T10:30:00.000Z',\n 244→  userId: '123456789',\n 245→  role: 'operator',\n 246→  action: 'stop',\n 247→  params: { type: 'feature' },\n 248→  result: 'success',\n 249→  reason: null,\n 250→  sessionId: 'telegram-123456789'\n 251→}\n 252→```\n 253→\n 254→**File Format**: JSON Lines (`.jsonl`)\n 255→```\n 256→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-XX T10:30:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"123456789\",...}\n 257→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-XX T10:31:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"987654321\",...}\n 258→```\n 259→\n 260→---\n 261→\n 262→## Integration Points\n 263→\n 264→### I-1: Command Handler Integration\n 265→\n 266→**Before (stop.js)**:\n 267→```javascript\n 268→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 269→  const { params, reply } = handlerCtx;\n 270→  const result = await stopPipeline({ type: pipelineType });\n 271→  // ...\n 272→}\n 273→```\n 274→\n 275→**After (stop.js)**:\n 276→```javascript\n 277→import { checkCommandPermission, getUserRole } from '../../security/permission-guard.js';\n 278→import { createConfirmation, checkConfirmation } from '../../security/confirmation-manager.js';\n 279→import { sanitizeParam } from '../../security/param-sanitizer.js';\n 280→import { logAuditEntry } from '../../services/audit-log-service.js';\n 281→\n 282→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 283→  const { params, reply, userId, session } = handlerCtx;\n 284→  \n 285→  // 1. Permission check\n 286→  const perm = checkCommandPermission(userId, 'stop');\n 287→  if (!perm.allowed) {\n 288→    await logAuditEntry({ userId, action: 'stop', params, result: 'denied', reason: perm.reason });\n 289→    await reply('⛔ 权限不足');\n 290→    return;\n 291→  }\n 292→  \n 293→  // 2. Parameter sanitization\n 294→  const type = sanitizeParam(params.type || 'feature', { maxLength: 50 });\n 295→  if (!type.ok) {\n 296→    await reply(`❌ 参数无效: ${type.error}`);\n 297→    return;\n 298→  }\n 299→  \n 300→  // 3. Confirmation (if required)\n 301→  if (perm.requiresConfirmation) {\n 302→    const confirm = await handleConfirmation(handlerCtx, 'stop', { type: type.value });\n 303→    if (!confirm.confirmed) return;\n 304→  }\n 305→  \n 306→  // 4. Execute\n 307→  const result = await stopPipeline({ type: type.value });\n 308→  await logAuditEntry({ userId, action: 'stop', params, result: result.ok ? 'success' : 'failed' });\n 309→  // ...\n 310→}\n 311→```\n 312→\n 313→### I-2: Config Extension (`src/config.js`)\n 314→\n 315→```javascript\n 316→// Add to schema\n 317→USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 318→ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 319→AUDIT_LOG_DIR: z.string().optional().default('logs'),\n 320→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n 321→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(5),\n 322→\n 323→// Add to config export\n 324→userPermissions: parseUserPermissions(parsed.USER_PERMISSIONS),\n 325→allowAdminSkipConfirm: parseBoolean(parsed.ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM),\n 326→auditLogDir: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_DIR,\n 327→auditLogMaxSizeMb: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB,\n 328→auditLogMaxFiles: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES,\n 329→```\n 330→\n 331→---\n 332→\n 333→## Test Strategy\n 334→\n 335→### Unit Tests\n 336→\n 337→| Module | Test Cases |\n 338→|--------|------------|\n 339→| permission-guard | Role hierarchy, permission matrix, default viewer |\n 340→| param-sanitizer | Dangerous patterns, path validation, length limits |\n 341→| confirmation-manager | Create/confirm/expire/cancel flows |\n 342→| audit-log-service | Write, query, rotation |\n 343→\n 344→### Integration Tests\n 345→\n 346→| Scenario | Validation |\n 347→|----------|------------|\n 348→| Operator stop flow | Permission → Confirm → Execute → Log |\n 349→| Viewer denied | Returns denied message, logs denial |\n 350→| Dangerous param rejected | Shell injection blocked |\n 351→| Audit query by user | Returns correct entries |\n 352→\n 353→---\n 354→\n 355→## Risks & Mitigations\n 356→\n 357→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 358→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 359→| Confirmation timeout during network issues | Medium | Low | Allow re-initiation, log timeout |\n 360→| Audit log disk full | Low | Medium | Rotation + size limit + async write |\n 361→| Permission config error | Medium | High | Default to most restrictive, validate on startup |\n 362→\n 363→---\n 364→\n 365→## File Changes Summary\n 366→\n 367→| File | Action | Purpose |\n 368→|------|--------|---------|\n 369→| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | NEW | Permission tiers & command auth |\n 370→| `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` | NEW | Parameter sanitization |\n 371→| `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` | NEW | Confirmation flow |\n 372→| `src/services/audit-log-service.js` | NEW | Audit logging |\n 373→| `src/config.js` | MODIFY | Add security config |\n 374→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 375→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 376→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` | MODIFY | Integrate security guard |\n 377→| `src/security/index.js` | NEW | Security module exports |\n 378→| `tests/security/*.test.js` | NEW | Unit tests |\n 379→| `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js` | NEW | Integration tests |\n 380→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde9b972165b5f35eeda38e0e2170","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:34:39.856Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
