middleware\n  89→  - Input: Command context with userId\n  90→  - Output: Permission check before handler execution\n  91→  - Acceptance: All commands protected\n  92→  - Complexity: Medium\n  93→  - Depends: T-010, T-011\n  94→\n  95→### US-2: Command Whitelist\n  96→\n  97→- [ ] [T-102] [US-2] [P] Add minRole metadata to all command handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n  98→  - Goal: Define required role for each command\n  99→  - Input: Command definitions\n 100→  - Output: Updated command metadata\n 101→  - Acceptance: All commands have minRole\n 102→  - Complexity: Low\n 103→  - Depends: T-001\n 104→\n 105→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n 106→\n 107→- [ ] [T-103] [US-3] Integrate param sanitizer into handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js, bugfix.js, stop.js\n 108→  - Note: force-unlock command logic will be added to pipeline.js (no separate lock.js needed)\n 109→  - Goal: Sanitize all input parameters\n 110→  - Input: Raw command params\n 111→  - Output: Sanitized params or error\n 112→  - Acceptance: No injection vectors\n 113→  - Complexity: Medium\n 114→  - Depends: T-012, T-013\n 115→\n 116→### US-4: Confirmation Flow\n 117→\n 118→- [ ] [T-104] [US-4] Implement confirmation flow (text-based per D2) — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js, pipeline.js\n 119→  - Goal: Add confirmation buttons for high-risk actions\n 120→  - Input: Confirmation request\n 121→  - Output: Inline keyboard with confirm/cancel\n 122→  - Acceptance: Buttons trigger correct callbacks\n 123→  - Complexity: Medium\n 124→  - Depends: T-014\n 125→\n 126→- [ ] [T-105] [US-4] Add force-unlock command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n 127→  - Goal: Handle confirm/cancel button clicks\n 128→  - Input: Telegram callback query\n 129→  - Output: Execute or cancel action\n 130→  - Acceptance: Correct action execution flow\n 131→  - Complexity: Medium\n 132→  - Depends: T-104\n 133→\n 134→- [ ] [T-106] [US-4] Integrate confirmation into stop handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n 135→  - Goal: Add confirmation for stop command\n 136→  - Input: Stop command request\n 137→  - Output: Confirmation flow then execution\n 138→  - Acceptance: Operator sees confirmation, admin can skip\n 139→  - Complexity: Medium\n 140→  - Depends: T-104, T-105\n 141→\n 142→### US-5: Audit Logging\n 143→\n 144→- [ ] [T-107] [US-5] [P] Add audit logging to all sensitive handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n 145→  - Goal: Log all sensitive operations\n 146→  - Input: Operation context\n 147→  - Output: Audit log entries\n 148→  - Acceptance: All high-risk commands logged\n 149→  - Complexity: Low\n 150→  - Depends: T-016, T-017\n 151→\n 152→- [ ] [T-108] [US-5] Create `/audit` command for log query — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 153→  - Goal: Allow admins to query audit logs\n 154→  - Input: Query filters via command params\n 155→  - Output: Formatted audit log entries\n 156→  - Acceptance: Admin-only, filterable results\n 157→  - Complexity: Medium\n 158→  - Depends: T-016\n 159→\n 160→---\n 161→\n 162→## Phase 4: Integration & Polish (T-900+)\n 163→\n 164→- [ ] [T-901] Create integration test for full security flow — file: tests/integration/security-flow.test.js\n 165→  - Goal: End-to-end security flow validation\n 166→  - Input: Simulated Telegram commands\n 167→  - Output: Full flow coverage\n 168→  - Acceptance: All user stories validated\n 169→  - Complexity: High\n 170→  - Depends: T-101, T-103, T-106, T-107\n 171→\n 172→- [ ] [T-902] [P] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with security module — file: .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n 173→  - Goal: Document security module in L1 doc\n 174→  - Input: New security files\n 175→  - Output: Updated DECISIONS and SUBDIRS\n 176→  - Acceptance: Security module documented\n 177→  - Complexity: Low\n 178→\n 179→- [ ] [T-903] [P] Create `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` L2 doc — file: .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n 180→  - Goal: Document security module details\n 181→  - Input: Security implementation\n 182→  - Output: L2 Prizm doc with KEY_FILES, INTERFACES, TRAPS\n 183→  - Acceptance: All security files documented\n 184→  - Complexity: Low\n 185→\n 186→---\n 187→\n 188→## Dependency Graph\n 189→\n 190→```\n 191→T-001 ──┬── T-010 ── T-011 ── T-101\n 192→        │\n 193→        └── T-012 ── T-013 ── T-103\n 194→\n 195→T-002 ──── T-016 ── T-017 ── T-107\n 196→                      │\n 197→                      └── T-108\n 198→\n 199→T-003 (parallel)\n 200→\n 201→T-014 ── T-015 ── T-104 ── T-105 ── T-106\n 202→\n 203→T-901 depends on: T-101, T-103, T-106, T-107\n 204→T-902, T-903 (parallel, can start after core modules complete)\n 205→```\n 206→\n 207→---\n 208→\n 209→## Parallel Execution Groups\n 210→\n 211→| Group | Tasks | Can Run In Parallel |\n 212→|-------|-------|---------------------|\n 213→| G1 | T-001, T-002, T-003 | ✓ (all setup tasks) |\n 214→| G2 | T-010, T-012 | ✓ (independent modules) |\n 215→| G3 | T-102, T-107 | ✓ (metadata additions) |\n 216→| G4 | T-902, T-903 | ✓ (documentation) |\n 217→\n 218→---\n 219→\n 220→## Summary\n 221→\n 222→| Phase | Task Count | Estimated Complexity |\n 223→|-------|------------|---------------------|\n 224→| Setup | 3 | Low |\n 225→| Foundational | 8 | Medium |\n 226→| User Stories | 8 | Medium-High |\n 227→| Polish | 3 | Low-Medium |\n 228→| **Total** | **22** | |\n 229→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde9b972165b5f35eeda38e0e2170","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:34:39.858Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"39351522-bb49-4fb2-8d10-3b5dcbe17de7","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4089e8cf2c904ce3bbe73c7e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→为 Telegram 管道控制增加安全护栏：用户权限分级、高风险命令授权校验、参数净化、敏感操作二次确认与审计日志。重点覆盖 stop/reset/retry/exec 等高风险指令，确保\"可用\"与\"可控\"并存。\n   6→\n   7→**Scope**: 权限分级模型、高风险命令拦截、参数净化、确认机制、审计日志。\n   8→\n   9→**Dependencies**: F-002 (Telegram Pipeline Command Router - completed), F-004 (Pipeline Process Controller - completed)\n  10→\n  11→---\n  12→\n  13→## User Stories\n  14→\n  15→### US-1: User Permission Levels\n  16→\n  17→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 基于用户 ID 的权限分级机制 **So that** 不同用户拥有不同的操作权限\n  18→\n  19→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  20→- AC-1.1: 支持三级权限: `admin` | `operator` | `viewer`\n  21→- AC-1.2: 通过环境变量 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 配置用户权限映射\n  22→- AC-1.3: 未配置时所有授权用户默认为 `operator`\n  23→- AC-1.4: 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` API 查询用户权限级别\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 高风险命令需要特定权限级别才能执行 **So that** 敏感操作不会被未授权用户触发\n  28→\n  29→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  30→- AC-2.1: 定义高风险命令列表: `stop`, `reset`, `retry`, `exec`, `force-unlock`\n  31→- AC-2.2: `stop`/`reset`/`force-unlock` 需要 `admin` 权限\n  32→- AC-2.3: `retry` 需要 `operator` 权限\n  33→- AC-2.4: `exec` 需要 `admin` 权限且受 `ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC` 控制\n  34→- AC-2.5: 权限不足时返回统一拒绝消息，不暴露敏感信息\n  35→\n  36→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n  37→\n  38→**As a** 系统 **I want** 所有命令参数经过净化与规则校验 **So that** 非法路径与危险参数组合被拒绝\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  41→- AC-3.1: 路径参数禁止 `..`、绝对路径穿越、shell 元字符\n  42→- AC-3.2: targetId 参数仅允许 `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+` 格式\n  43→- AC-3.3: 拒绝包含 `; | & $ \\` ' \" ( ) < >` 等危险字符的参数\n  44→- AC-3.4: 提供 `sanitizePath()` 和 `sanitizeTargetId()` 工具函数\n  45→\n  46→### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n  47→\n  48→**As a** 用户 **I want** 高风险命令执行前需要明确确认 **So that** 误操作可以被及时阻止\n  49→\n  50→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  51→- AC-4.1: `stop`、`reset`、`force-unlock` 需要二次确认\n  52→- AC-4.2: 确认消息包含操作摘要和风险提示\n  53→- AC-4.3: 用户需在 60 秒内回复确认，否则操作取消\n  54→- AC-4.4: 支持 `--force` 标志跳过确认（仅限 `admin` 用户）\n  55→\n  56→### US-5: Audit Logging\n  57→\n  58→**As a** 运维人员 **I want** 每次敏感操作都写入审计日志 **So that** 我可以追溯操作历史\n  59→\n  60→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  61→- AC-5.1: 审计日志记录: timestamp, userId, username, action, params, result\n  62→- AC-5.2: 日志存储于 `logs/audit.log`（JSON Lines 格式）\n  63→- AC-5.3: 提供按会话 ID 或用户 ID 检索审计记录的 API\n  64→- AC-5.4: 日志轮转: 单文件最大 10MB，保留最近 5 个文件\n  65→\n  66→---\n  67→\n  68→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  69→\n  70→- **NFR-1 Performance**: 权限检查 < 5ms，参数净化 < 2ms，审计日志异步写入\n  71→- **NFR-2 Reliability**: 审计日志写入失败不影响命令执行，确认超时无死锁\n  72→- **NFR-3 Maintainability**: 权限配置与代码分离，高风险命令列表可配置，测试覆盖率 > 90%\n  73→- **NFR-4 Security**: 不在错误消息中暴露内部路径或配置，审计日志不可被普通用户访问\n  74→\n  75→---\n  76→\n  77→## Scope Boundaries\n  78→\n  79→**In Scope**: 用户权限分级模型与配置、高风险命令授权检查中间件、参数净化工具函数、确认对话机制、审计日志服务\n  80→\n  81→**Out of Scope**: 用户认证（已有 `isAllowedUser`）、Web UI 权限管理、数据库存储、加密存储\n  82→\n  83→---\n  84→\n  85→## High-Risk Command Matrix\n  86→\n  87→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation | Notes |\n  88→|---------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n  89→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 停止运行中管道 |\n  90→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 重置管道状态 |\n  91→| `retry` | operator | No | 重试失败目标 |\n  92→| `exec` | admin | No | 执行系统命令 |\n  93→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 强制释放锁 |\n  94→\n  95→---\n  96→\n  97→## Configuration\n  98→\n  99→```env\n 100→USER_PERMISSIONS=123456789:admin,987654321:operator\n 101→AUDIT_LOG_DIR=logs\n 102→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB=10\n 103→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES=5\n 104→```\n 105→\n 106→---\n 107→\n 108→## Decisions\n 109→\n 110→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 111→|----|------|----------|\n 112→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用三级权限模型（admin/operator/viewer）|\n 113→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 确认机制使用文字确认（\"CONFIRM\"），不依赖 inline keyboard |\n 114→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 审计日志使用 JSON Lines 格式 |\n 115→| D4 | 2026-03-12 | `--force` 标志仅限 admin 用户 |\n 116→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde9b972165b5f35eeda38e0e2170","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:34:39.858Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
