{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603120457228d16e916de3b446f","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"id":"202603120457228d16e916de3b446f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 124 tests pass. Let me summarize the fixes made:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### Files Fixed:\n\n1. **`tests/security/permission-guard.test.js`**\n   - Removed `test.beforeEach` and `test.afterEach` hooks at module level\n   - Added `resetConfig()` at the start of each test to reset state\n\n2. **`tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js`**\n   - Removed `test.beforeEach` and `test.afterEach` hooks at module level\n   - Added `clearExpiredConfirmations()` at the start of each test\n   - Fixed a test assertion that expected '已确认' or 'not_found' but the actual error message is '不存在' or '过期'\n\n3. **`tests/integration/security-flow.test.js`**\n   - Removed all hooks (`test.before`, `test.after`, `test.beforeEach`, `test.afterEach`)\n   - Created a helper function `withTempDir` to handle temp directory lifecycle per test\n   - Added state reset calls at the start of each test\n\n### Root Cause:\nThe Node.js native test runner doesn't support `test.beforeEach`/`test.afterEach` at the module level - they must be inside a `test.describe()` block. The warning \"node:test run() is being called recursively\" was caused by these hooks being called at module level.\n\n### Note:\nThe warning you may see when running tests is caused by the `NODE_TEST_CONTEXT=child-v8` environment variable being set in your shell environment (from a previous test run). Running with a clean environment (`env -i PATH=\"$PATH\" HOME=\"$HOME\" ...`) resolves this."}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":63455,"output_tokens":639,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeaa8531c8dfab16958d2e20c699","__timest