{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312045747e6e197728ef54142","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"id":"20260312045747e6e197728ef54142","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_4f928532e1f345f08bbfacfb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/integration/security-flow.test.js"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":10911,"output_tokens":283,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:57:55.517Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"08e0eda7-4e66-43a9-8b52-0b0c939d6a09","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2f32f5812c6149a8916f0543","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→\n  46→### 行为规则\n  47→\n  48→```\n  49→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  50→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  51→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  52→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  53→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  54→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  55→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  56→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  57→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  58→```\n  59→\n  60→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  61→\n  62→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  63→\n  64→1. 运行 `prizmkit.analyze`（只读）\n  65→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  66→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  67→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  68→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  69→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  70→\n  71→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  72→\n  73→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  74→\n  75→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  76→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  77→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  78→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  79→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  80→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  81→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  82→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  83→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  84→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  85→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  86→\n  87→### 判定标准\n  88→\n  89→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  90→|------|------|---------|\n  91→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  92→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  93→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  94→\n  95→### 严重级别\n  96→\n  97→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n  98→|------|------|------|\n  99→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 100→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 101→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 102→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 103→\n 104→### 异常处理\n 105→\n 106→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 107→|------|------|\n 108→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 109→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 110→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 111→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 112→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 113→\n 114→### 通信规则\n 115→\n 116→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 117→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 118→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 119→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 120→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:57:55.518Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"85a37a37-1459-4791-8e7a-ffa6dd40abb3","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f69c631c33b24aea94dcb75e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n   2→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n   3→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n   4→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n   5→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n   6→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n   7→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n   8→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n   9→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n  10→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n  11→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n  12→\n  13→MODULE_INDEX:\n  14→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n  15→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n  16→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n  17→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n  18→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n  19→\n  20→LOAD_RULES:\n  21→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n  22→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n  23→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n  24→\n  25→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n  26→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n  27→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n  28→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:57:55.518Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"41a31e96-2e3a-48d7-bb53-10106dde5298","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c1b6c87e6fd549cb86e87027","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→为 Telegram 管道控制增加安全护栏：用户权限分级、高风险命令授权校验、参数净化、敏感操作二次确认与审计日志。重点覆盖 stop/reset/retry/exec 等高风险指令，确保\"可用\"与\"可控\"并存。\n   6→\n   7→**Scope**: 权限分级模型、高风险命令拦截、参数净化、确认机制、审计日志。\n   8→\n   9→**Dependencies**: F-002 (Telegram Pipeline Command Router - completed), F-004 (Pipeline Process Controller - completed)\n  10→\n  11→---\n  12→\n  13→## User Stories\n  14→\n  15→### US-1: User Permission Levels\n  16→\n  17→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 基于用户 ID 的权限分级机制 **So that** 不同用户拥有不同的操作权限\n  18→\n  19→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  20→- AC-1.1: 支持三级权限: `admin` | `operator` | `viewer`\n  21→- AC-1.2: 通过环境变量 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 配置用户权限映射\n  22→- AC-1.3: 未配置时所有授权用户默认为 `operator`\n  23→- AC-1.4: 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` API 查询用户权限级别\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 高风险命令需要特定权限级别才能执行 **So that** 敏感操作不会被未授权用户触发\n  28→\n  29→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  30→- AC-2.1: 定义高风险命令列表: `stop`, `reset`, `retry`, `exec`, `force-unlock`\n  31→- AC-2.2: `stop`/`reset`/`force-unlock` 需要 `admin` 权限\n  32→- AC-2.3: `retry` 需要 `operator` 权限\n  33→- AC-2.4: `exec` 需要 `admin` 权限且受 `ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC` 控制\n  34→- AC-2.5: 权限不足时返回统一拒绝消息，不暴露敏感信息\n  35→\n  36→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n  37→\n  38→**As a** 系统 **I want** 所有命令参数经过净化与规则校验 **So that** 非法路径与危险参数组合被拒绝\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  41→- AC-3.1: 路径参数禁止 `..`、绝对路径穿越、shell 元字符\n  42→- AC-3.2: targetId 参数仅允许 `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+` 格式\n  43→- AC-3.3: 拒绝包含 `; | & $ \\` ' \" ( ) < >` 等危险字符的参数\n  44→- AC-3.4: 提供 `sanitizePath()` 和 `sanitizeTargetId()` 工具函数\n  45→\n  46→### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n  47→\n  48→**As a** 用户 **I want** 高风险命令执行前需要明确确认 **So that** 误操作可以被及时阻止\n  49→\n  50→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  51→- AC-4.1: `stop`、`reset`、`force-unlock` 需要二次确认\n  52→- AC-4.2: 确认消息包含操作摘要和风险提示\n  53→- AC-4.3: 用户需在 60 秒内回复确认，否则操作取消\n  54→- AC-4.4: 支持 `--force` 标志跳过确认（仅限 `admin` 用户）\n  55→\n  56→### US-5: Audit Logging\n  57→\n  58→**As a** 运维人员 **I want** 每次敏感操作都写入审计日志 **So that** 我可以追溯操作历史\n  59→\n  60→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  61→- AC-5.1: 审计日志记录: timestamp, userId, username, action, params, result\n  62→- AC-5.2: 日志存储于 `logs/audit.log`（JSON Lines 格式）\n  63→- AC-5.3: 提供按会话 ID 或用户 ID 检索审计记录的 API\n  64→- AC-5.4: 日志轮转: 单文件最大 10MB，保留最近 5 个文件\n  65→\n  66→---\n  67→\n  68→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  69→\n  70→- **NFR-1 Performance**: 权限检查 < 5ms，参数净化 < 2ms，审计日志异步写入\n  71→- **NFR-2 Reliability**: 审计日志写入失败不影响命令执行，确认超时无死锁\n  72→- **NFR-3 Maintainability**: 权限配置与代码分离，高风险命令列表可配置，测试覆盖率 > 90%\n  73→- **NFR-4 Security**: 不在错误消息中暴露内部路径或配置，审计日志不可被普通用户访问\n  74→\n  75→---\n  76→\n  77→## Scope Boundaries\n  78→\n  79→**In Scope**: 用户权限分级模型与配置、高风险命令授权检查中间件、参数净化工具函数、确认对话机制、审计日志服务\n  80→\n  81→**Out of Scope**: 用户认证（已有 `isAllowedUser`）、Web UI 权限管理、数据库存储、加密存储\n  82→\n  83→---\n  84→\n  85→## High-Risk Command Matrix\n  86→\n  87→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation | Notes |\n  88→|---------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n  89→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 停止运行中管道 |\n  90→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 重置管道状态 |\n  91→| `retry` | operator | No | 重试失败目标 |\n  92→| `exec` | admin | No | 执行系统命令 |\n  93→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 强制释放锁 |\n  94→\n  95→---\n  96→\n  97→## Configuration\n  98→\n  99→```env\n 100→USER_PERMISSIONS=123456789:admin,987654321:operator\n 101→AUDIT_LOG_DIR=logs\n 102→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB=10\n 103→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES=5\n 104→```\n 105→\n 106→---\n 107→\n 108→## Decisions\n 109→\n 110→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 111→|----|------|----------|\n 112→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用三级权限模型（admin/operator/viewer）|\n 113→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 确认机制使用文字确认（\"CONFIRM\"），不依赖 inline keyboard |\n 114→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 审计日志使用 JSON Lines 格式 |\n 115→| D4 | 2026-03-12 | `--force` 标志仅限 admin 用户 |\n 116→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:57:55.519Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"58148ad7-594a-42ce-8619-8e3a31b7893c","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4f928532e1f345f08bbfacfb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Integration Test for F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   3→ * Tests the full security flow end-to-end.\n   4→ */\n   5→\n   6→import test from 'node:test';\n   7→import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n   8→import { mkdtemp, rm } from 'node:fs/promises';\n   9→import { join } from 'node:path';\n  10→import { tmpdir } from 'node:os';\n  11→import {\n  12→  checkCommandPermission,\n  13→  getUserRole,\n  14→  isAdmin,\n  15→  setConfigForTesting,\n  16→  resetConfig as resetPermConfig\n  17→} from '../../src/security/permission-guard.js';\n  18→import {\n  19→  createConfirmation,\n  20→  checkConfirmation,\n  21→  confirmAction,\n  22→  cancelConfirmation,\n  23→  clearExpiredConfirmations\n  24→} from '../../src/security/confirmation-manager.js';\n  25→import { sanitizeParam, validatePath, detectDangerousPatterns } from '../../src/security/param-sanitizer.js';\n  26→import {\n  27→  initAuditLogService,\n  28→  logAuditEntry,\n  29→  queryAuditLogs,\n  30→  resetAuditLogService\n  31→} from '../../src/services/audit-log-service.js';\n  32→\n  33→// Helper to create test config\n  34→function createTestConfig(overrides = {}) {\n  35→  return {\n  36→    userPermissions: new Map(),\n  37→    allowAdminSkipConfirm: true,\n  38→    enableSystemExec: false,\n  39→    allowedUserIds: new Set(),\n  40→    ...overrides\n  41→  };\n  42→}\n  43→\n  44→// Helper to create temp directory for audit log tests\n  45→async function withTempDir(fn) {\n  46→  const tempDir = await mkdtemp(join(tmpdir(), 'security-integration-'));\n  47→  try {\n  48→    return await fn(tempDir);\n  49→  } finally {\n  50→    await rm(tempDir, { recursive: true, force: true });\n  51→  }\n  52→}\n  53→\n  54→// US-1: User Permission Levels\n  55→test('US-1: User permission levels work correctly', async () => {\n  56→  resetPermConfig();\n  57→  resetAuditLogService();\n  58→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n  59→\n  60→  const config = createTestConfig();\n  61→  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n  62→  config.userPermissions.set('op-user', 'operator');\n  63→  config.userPermissions.set('viewer-user', 'viewer');\n  64→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n  65→\n  66→  // Test role retrieval\n  67→  assert.equal(getUserRole('admin-user'), 'admin');\n  68→  assert.equal(getUserRole('op-user'), 'operator');\n  69→  assert.equal(getUserRole('viewer-user'), 'viewer');\n  70→  assert.equal(getUserRole('unknown-user'), 'operator'); // Default\n  71→\n  72→  // Test isAdmin\n  73→  assert.equal(isAdmin('admin-user'), true);\n  74→  assert.equal(isAdmin('op-user'), false);\n  75→  assert.equal(isAdmin('viewer-user'), false);\n  76→});\n  77→\n  78→// US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  79→test('US-2: High-risk command authorization works correctly', async () => {\n  80→  resetPermConfig();\n  81→  resetAuditLogService();\n  82→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n  83→\n  84→  const config = createTestConfig();\n  85→  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n  86→  config.userPermissions.set('op-user', 'operator');\n  87→  config.userPermissions.set('viewer-user', 'viewer');\n  88→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n  89→\n  90→  // stop command - admin only\n  91→  const adminStopResult = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'stop');\n  92→  assert.equal(adminStopResult.allowed, true);\n  93→  assert.equal(adminStopResult.requiresConfirmation, true);\n  94→\n  95→  const opStopResult = checkCommandPermission('op-user', 'stop');\n  96→  assert.equal(opStopResult.allowed, false);\n  97→\n  98→  // retry command - operator level\n  99→  const opRetryResult = checkCommandPermission('op-user', 'retry');\n 100→  assert.equal(opRetryResult.allowed, true);\n 101→  assert.equal(opRetryResult.requiresConfirmation, false);\n 102→\n 103→  const viewerRetryResult = checkCommandPermission('viewer-user', 'retry');\n 104→  assert.equal(viewerRetryResult.allowed, false);\n 105→});\n 106→\n 107→// US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n 108→test('US-3: Parameter sanitization works correctly', async () => {\n 109→  resetPermConfig();\n 110→  resetAuditLogService();\n 111→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 112→\n 113→  // Valid input passes\n 114→  const validResult = sanitizeParam('my-feature-123', { maxLength: 100 });\n 115→  assert.equal(validResult.ok, true);\n 116→\n 117→  // Dangerous patterns are blocked\n 118→  const traversalResult = sanitizeParam('../../../etc/passwd');\n 119→  assert.equal(traversalResult.ok, false);\n 120→\n 121→  const shellInjectionResult = sanitizeParam('$(whoami)');\n 122→  assert.equal(shellInjectionResult.ok, false);\n 123→\n 124→  // TargetId format validation\n 125→  const validTargetId = sanitizeParam('feature-branch_123', { isTargetId: true });\n 126→  assert.equal(validTargetId.ok, true);\n 127→\n 128→  const invalidTargetId = sanitizeParam('feature/branch', { isTargetId: true });\n 129→  assert.equal(invalidTargetId.ok, false);\n 130→\n 131→  // Path validation\n 132→  const validPath = validatePath('/project/src/file.js', ['/project']);\n 133→  assert.equal(validPath.ok, true);\n 134→\n 135→  const invalidPath = validatePath('/etc/passwd', ['/project']);\n 136→  assert.equal(invalidPath.ok, false);\n 137→});\n 138→\n 139→// US-4: Confirmation Flow\n 140→test('US-4: Confirmation flow works correctly', async () => {\n 141→  resetPermConfig();\n 142→  resetAuditLogService();\n 143→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 144→\n 145→  // Create confirmation\n 146→  const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation('test-user', 'stop', { type: 'feature' });\n 147→  assert.ok(confirmId);\n 148→  assert.ok(message);\n 149→\n 150→  // Check pending status\n 151→  const pendingResult = checkConfirmation(confirmId, 'test-user');\n 152→  assert.equal(pendingResult.status, 'pending');\n 153→  assert.equal(pendingResult.action, 'stop');\n 154→\n 155→  // Confirm action\n 156→  const confirmResult = confirmAction(confirmId, 'test-user');\n 157→  assert.equal(confirmResult.ok, true);\n 158→  assert.equal(confirmResult.action, 'stop');\n 159→\n 160→  // Verify consumed\n 161→  const consumedResult = checkConfirmation(confirmId, 'test-user');\n 162→  assert.equal(consumedResult.status, 'not_found');\n 163→});\n 164→\n 165→test('US-4: Confirmation cancel works correctly', () => {\n 166→  resetPermConfig();\n 167→  resetAuditLogService();\n 168→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 169→\n 170→  const { confirmId } = createConfirmation('test-user', 'reset', {});\n 171→\n 172→  cancelConfirmation(confirmId, 'test-user');\n 173→\n 174→  const result = checkConfirmation(confirmId, 'test-user');\n 175→  assert.equal(result.status, 'not_found');\n 176→});\n 177→\n 178→test('US-4: Wrong user cannot confirm', () => {\n 179→  resetPermConfig();\n 180→  resetAuditLogService();\n 181→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 182→\n 183→  const { confirmId } = createConfirmation('user-1', 'stop', {});\n 184→\n 185→  const result = confirmAction(confirmId, 'user-2');\n 186→  assert.equal(result.ok, false);\n 187→});\n 188→\n 189→// US-5: Audit Logging\n 190→test('US-5: Audit logging works correctly', async () => {\n 191→  resetPermConfig();\n 192→  resetAuditLogService();\n 193→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 194→\n 195→  await withTempDir(async (tempDir) => {\n 196→    await initAuditLogService({ logDir: tempDir, maxFileSizeMb: 10, maxFiles: 5 });\n 197→\n 198→    // Log entry\n 199→    await logAuditEntry({\n 200→      userId: '123456789',\n 201→      action: 'stop',\n 202→      params: { type: 'feature' },\n 203→      result: 'success'\n 204→    });\n 205→\n 206→    // Query logs\n 207→    const entries = await queryAuditLogs({ userId: '123456789' });\n 208→    assert.ok(entries.length >= 1);\n 209→\n 210→    const entry = entries.find((e) => e.action === 'stop');\n 211→    assert.ok(entry);\n 212→    assert.equal(entry.userId, '123456789');\n 213→    assert.equal(entry.result, 'success');\n 214→  });\n 215→});\n 216→\n 217→test('US-5: Audit log query filters work', async () => {\n 218→  resetPermConfig();\n 219→  resetAuditLogService();\n 220→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 221→\n 222→  await withTempDir(async (tempDir) => {\n 223→    await initAuditLogService({ logDir: tempDir, maxFileSizeMb: 10, maxFiles: 5 });\n 224→\n 225→    await logAuditEntry({ userId: 'user-1', action: 'stop', params: {}, result: 'success' });\n 226→    await logAuditEntry({ userId: 'user-1', action: 'reset', params: {}, result: 'success' });\n 227→    await logAuditEntry({ userId: 'user-2', action: 'stop', params: {}, result: 'denied' });\n 228→\n 229→    const user1Entries = await queryAuditLogs({ userId: 'user-1' });\n 230→    assert.ok(user1Entries.every((e) => e.userId === 'user-1'));\n 231→\n 232→    const stopEntries = await queryAuditLogs({ action: 'stop' });\n 233→    assert.ok(stopEntries.every((e) => e.action === 'stop'));\n 234→  });\n 235→});\n 236→\n 237→// F-001: force-unlock command\n 238→test('F-001: force-unlock command requires admin and confirmation', async () => {\n 239→  resetPermConfig();\n 240→  resetAuditLogService();\n 241→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 242→\n 243→  const config = createTestConfig();\n 244→  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n 245→  config.userPermissions.set('op-user', 'operator');\n 246→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n 247→\n 248→  const adminResult = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'force-unlock');\n 249→  assert.equal(adminResult.allowed, true);\n 250→  assert.equal(adminResult.requiresConfirmation, true);\n 251→\n 252→  const opResult = checkCommandPermission('op-user', 'force-unlock');\n 253→  assert.equal(opResult.allowed, false);\n 254→});\n 255→\n 256→// F-002: exec command with ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC\n 257→test('F-002: exec command requires ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC', async () => {\n 258→  resetPermConfig();\n 259→  resetAuditLogService();\n 260→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 261→\n 262→  const config = createTestConfig({ enableSystemExec: false });\n 263→  config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n 264→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n 265→\n 266→  const disabledResult = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'exec');\n 267→  assert.equal(disabledResult.allowed, false);\n 268→  assert.ok(disabledResult.reason.includes('系统命令执行未启用'));\n 269→\n 270→  // Enable system exec\n 271→  config.enableSystemExec = true;\n 272→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n 273→\n 274→  const enabledResult = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'exec');\n 275→  assert.equal(enabledResult.allowed, true);\n 276→});\n 277→\n 278→// Full flow test: Operator stop flow (should be denied)\n 279→test('Integration: Operator cannot execute stop command', async () => {\n 280→  resetPermConfig();\n 281→  resetAuditLogService();\n 282→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 283→\n 284→  await withTempDir(async (tempDir) => {\n 285→    const config = createTestConfig();\n 286→    config.userPermissions.set('op-user', 'operator');\n 287→    setConfigForTesting(config);\n 288→\n 289→    const result = checkCommandPermission('op-user', 'stop');\n 290→    assert.equal(result.allowed, false);\n 291→\n 292→    // Log denial\n 293→    await initAuditLogService({ logDir: tempDir });\n 294→    await logAuditEntry({\n 295→      userId: 'op-user',\n 296→      action: 'stop',\n 297→      params: {},\n 298→      result: 'denied',\n 299→      reason: result.reason\n 300→    });\n 301→\n 302→    const entries = await queryAuditLogs({ action: 'stop', userId: 'op-user' });\n 303→    assert.ok(entries.some((e) => e.result === 'denied'));\n 304→  });\n 305→});\n 306→\n 307→// Full flow test: Admin stop with confirmation\n 308→test('Integration: Admin stop with confirmation flow', async () => {\n 309→  resetPermConfig();\n 310→  resetAuditLogService();\n 311→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 312→\n 313→  await withTempDir(async (tempDir) => {\n 314→    const config = createTestConfig();\n 315→    config.userPermissions.set('admin-user', 'admin');\n 316→    setConfigForTesting(config);\n 317→\n 318→    // 1. Check permission\n 319→    const permResult = checkCommandPermission('admin-user', 'stop');\n 320→    assert.equal(permResult.allowed, true);\n 321→    assert.equal(permResult.requiresConfirmation, true);\n 322→\n 323→    // 2. Create confirmation\n 324→    const { confirmId } = createConfirmation('admin-user', 'stop', { type: 'feature' });\n 325→\n 326→    // 3. Confirm\n 327→    const confirmResult = confirmAction(confirmId, 'admin-user');\n 328→    assert.equal(confirmResult.ok, true);\n 329→\n 330→    // 4. Log success\n 331→    await initAuditLogService({ logDir: tempDir });\n 332→    await logAuditEntry({\n 333→      userId: 'admin-user',\n 334→      action: 'stop',\n 335→      params: { type: 'feature' },\n 336→      result: 'success'\n 337→    });\n 338→\n 339→    const entries = await queryAuditLogs({ userId: 'admin-user', action: 'stop' });\n 340→    assert.ok(entries.some((e) => e.result === 'success'));\n 341→  });\n 342→});\n 343→\n 344→// AC-2.5: Error message security\n 345→test('AC-2.5: Error messages do not expose sensitive info', async () => {\n 346→  resetPermConfig();\n 347→  resetAuditLogService();\n 348→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 349→\n 350→  const config = createTestConfig();\n 351→  config.userPermissions.set('viewer-user', 'viewer');\n 352→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n 353→\n 354→  const result = checkCommandPermission('viewer-user', 'stop');\n 355→  assert.equal(result.allowed, false);\n 356→  assert.ok(!result.reason.includes('/'));\n 357→  assert.ok(!result.reason.includes('config'));\n 358→  assert.ok(!result.reason.includes('password'));\n 359→});\n 360→\n 361→// NFR-1: Performance\n 362→test('NFR-1: Permission check is fast', () => {\n 363→  resetPermConfig();\n 364→  resetAuditLogService();\n 365→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 366→\n 367→  const config = createTestConfig();\n 368→  config.userPermissions.set('test-user', 'admin');\n 369→  setConfigForTesting(config);\n 370→\n 371→  const start = Date.now();\n 372→  for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {\n 373→    checkCommandPermission('test-user', 'stop');\n 374→  }\n 375→  const duration = Date.now() - start;\n 376→\n 377→  // 1000 checks should take < 50ms total (< 0.05ms per check, well under 5ms requirement)\n 378→  assert.ok(duration < 50, `Permission check too slow: ${duration}ms for 1000 checks`);\n 379→});\n 380→\n 381→test('NFR-1: Param sanitization is fast', () => {\n 382→  resetPermConfig();\n 383→  resetAuditLogService();\n 384→  clearExpiredConfirmations();\n 385→\n 386→  const start = Date.now();\n 387→  for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {\n 388→    sanitizeParam('test-input-with-moderate-length', { maxLength: 100 });\n 389→  }\n 390→  const duration = Date.now() - start;\n 391→\n 392→  // 1000 sanitizations should take < 20ms total (< 0.02ms per check, well under 2ms requirement)\n 393→  assert.ok(duration < 20, `Sanitization too slow: ${duration}ms for 1000 checks`);\n 394→});\n 395→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:57:55.519Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
