ation behavior\n  41→  - Input: Various dangerous and safe inputs\n  42→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  43→  - Acceptance: Path traversal, shell injection, length limits tested\n  44→  - Complexity: Low\n  45→  - Depends: T-012\n  46→\n  47→### Confirmation Manager Module\n  48→\n  49→- [x] [T-014] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` core logic — file: src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n  50→  - Goal: Manage confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  51→  - Input: userId, action, params, timeout\n  52→  - Output: confirmId, status, action confirmation\n  53→  - Acceptance: Create/confirm/expire/cancel flows work\n  54→  - Complexity: Medium\n  55→\n  56→- [x] [T-015] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` unit tests — file: tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js\n  57→  - Goal: Verify confirmation lifecycle\n  58→  - Input: Various confirmation scenarios\n  59→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  60→  - Acceptance: Timeout, cancel, double-confirm tested\n  61→  - Complexity: Low\n  62→  - Depends: T-014\n  63→\n  64→### Audit Log Service\n  65→\n  66→- [x] [T-016] Implement `audit-log-service.js` core logic — file: src/services/audit-log-service.js\n  67→  - Goal: Write and query audit logs\n  68→  - Input: Audit entries, query filters\n  69→  - Output: JSON Lines log files\n  70→  - Acceptance: Async write, query by user/time/action\n  71→  - Complexity: Medium\n  72→\n  73→- [x] [T-017] Implement `audit-log-service.js` unit tests — file: tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js\n  74→  - Goal: Verify logging behavior\n  75→  - Input: Log entries, query parameters\n  76→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  77→  - Acceptance: Write, query, rotation tested\n  78→  - Complexity: Low\n  79→  - Depends: T-016\n  80→\n  81→---\n  82→\n  83→## Phase 3: User Stories (T-100+)\n  84→\n  85→### US-1: Permission Tiers\n  86→\n  87→- [x] [T-101] [US-1] Integrate permission guard into command registry — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  88→  - Goal: Add permission check middleware\n  89→  - Input: Command context with userId\n  90→  - Output: Permission check before handler execution\n  91→  - Acceptance: All commands protected\n  92→  - Complexity: Medium\n  93→  - Depends: T-010, T-011\n  94→\n  95→### US-2: Command Whitelist\n  96→\n  97→- [x] [T-102] [US-2] [P] Add minRole metadata to all command handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n  98→  - Goal: Define required role for each command\n  99→  - Input: Command definitions\n 100→  - Output: Updated command metadata\n 101→  - Acceptance: All commands have minRole\n 102→  - Complexity: Low\n 103→  - Depends: T-001\n 104→\n 105→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n 106→\n 107→- [x] [T-103] [US-3] Integrate param sanitizer into handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js, bugfix.js, stop.js\n 108→  - Note: force-unlock command logic will be added to pipeline.js (no separate lock.js needed)\n 109→  - Goal: Sanitize all input parameters\n 110→  - Input: Raw command params\n 111→  - Output: Sanitized params or error\n 112→  - Acceptance: No injection vectors\n 113→  - Complexity: Medium\n 114→  - Depends: T-012, T-013\n 115→\n 116→### US-4: Confirmation Flow\n 117→\n 118→- [x] [T-104] [US-4] Implement confirmation flow (text-based per D2) — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js, pipeline.js\n 119→  - Goal: Add confirmation buttons for high-risk actions\n 120→  - Input: Confirmation request\n 121→  - Output: Inline keyboard with confirm/cancel\n 122→  - Acceptance: Buttons trigger correct callbacks\n 123→  - Complexity: Medium\n 124→  - Depends: T-014\n 125→\n 126→- [x] [T-105] [US-4] Add force-unlock command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n 127→  - Goal: Handle confirm/cancel button clicks\n 128→  - Input: Telegram callback query\n 129→  - Output: Execute or cancel action\n 130→  - Acceptance: Correct action execution flow\n 131→  - Complexity: Medium\n 132→  - Depends: T-104\n 133→\n 134→- [x] [T-106] [US-4] Integrate confirmation into stop handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n 135→  - Goal: Add confirmation for stop command\n 136→  - Input: Stop command request\n 137→  - Output: Confirmation flow then execution\n 138→  - Acceptance: Operator sees confirmation, admin can skip\n 139→  - Complexity: Medium\n 140→  - Depends: T-104, T-105\n 141→\n 142→### US-5: Audit Logging\n 143→\n 144→- [x] [T-107] [US-5] [P] Add audit logging to all sensitive handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n 145→  - Goal: Log all sensitive operations\n 146→  - Input: Operation context\n 147→  - Output: Audit log entries\n 148→  - Acceptance: All high-risk commands logged\n 149→  - Complexity: Low\n 150→  - Depends: T-016, T-017\n 151→\n 152→- [x] [T-108] [US-5] Create `/audit` command for log query — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 153→  - Goal: Allow admins to query audit logs\n 154→  - Input: Query filters via command params\n 155→  - Output: Formatted audit log entries\n 156→  - Acceptance: Admin-only, filterable results\n 157→  - Complexity: Medium\n 158→  - Depends: T-016\n 159→\n 160→---\n 161→\n 162→## Phase 4: Integration & Polish (T-900+)\n 163→\n 164→- [x] [T-901] Create integration test for full security flow — file: tests/integration/security-flow.test.js\n 165→  - Goal: End-to-end security flow validation\n 166→  - Input: Simulated Telegram commands\n 167→  - Output: Full flow coverage\n 168→  - Acceptance: All user stories validated\n 169→  - Complexity: High\n 170→  - Depends: T-101, T-103, T-106, T-107\n 171→\n 172→- [x] [T-902] [P] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with security module — file: .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n 173→  - Goal: Document security module in L1 doc\n 174→  - Input: New security files\n 175→  - Output: Updated DECISIONS and SUBDIRS\n 176→  - Acceptance: Security module documented\n 177→  - Complexity: Low\n 178→\n 179→- [x] [T-903] [P] Create `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm` L2 doc — file: .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n 180→  - Goal: Document security module details\n 181→  - Input: Security implementation\n 182→  - Output: L2 Prizm doc with KEY_FILES, INTERFACES, TRAPS\n 183→  - Acceptance: All security files documented\n 184→  - Complexity: Low\n 185→\n 186→---\n 187→\n 188→## Dependency Graph\n 189→\n 190→```\n 191→T-001 ──┬── T-010 ── T-011 ── T-101\n 192→        │\n 193→        └── T-012 ── T-013 ── T-103\n 194→\n 195→T-002 ──── T-016 ── T-017 ── T-107\n 196→                      │\n 197→                      └── T-108\n 198→\n 199→T-003 (parallel)\n 200→\n 201→T-014 ── T-015 ── T-104 ── T-105 ── T-106\n 202→\n 203→T-901 depends on: T-101, T-103, T-106, T-107\n 204→T-902, T-903 (parallel, can start after core modules complete)\n 205→```\n 206→\n 207→---\n 208→\n 209→## Parallel Execution Groups\n 210→\n 211→| Group | Tasks | Can Run In Parallel |\n 212→|-------|-------|---------------------|\n 213→| G1 | T-001, T-002, T-003 | ✓ (all setup tasks) |\n 214→| G2 | T-010, T-012 | ✓ (independent modules) |\n 215→| G3 | T-102, T-107 | ✓ (metadata additions) |\n 216→| G4 | T-902, T-903 | ✓ (documentation) |\n 217→\n 218→---\n 219→\n 220→## Summary\n 221→\n 222→| Phase | Task Count | Estimated Complexity |\n 223→|-------|------------|---------------------|\n 224→| Setup | 3 | Low |\n 225→| Foundational | 8 | Medium |\n 226→| User Stories | 8 | Medium-High |\n 227→| Polish | 3 | Low-Medium |\n 228→| **Total** | **22** | |\n 229→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:58:03.570Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"625005e0-d2ed-4e7e-af8c-1a1ab3a86e95","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_00b39d9abc574fee941876b1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Permission Guard Module\n   3→ * F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   4→ *\n   5→ * Provides user permission tiers and command authorization checking.\n   6→ */\n   7→\n   8→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   9→\n  10→/**\n  11→ * Role hierarchy levels (higher = more permissions)\n  12→ */\n  13→export const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n  14→  viewer: 0,\n  15→  operator: 1,\n  16→  admin: 2\n  17→};\n  18→\n  19→/**\n  20→ * Minimum required role for each command\n  21→ */\n  22→const COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  23→  status: 'viewer',\n  24→  logs: 'viewer',\n  25→  pipeline: 'operator',\n  26→  bugfix: 'operator',\n  27→  planner: 'operator',\n  28→  retry: 'operator',\n  29→  stop: 'admin',\n  30→  reset: 'admin',\n  31→  'force-unlock': 'admin',\n  32→  exec: 'admin'\n  33→};\n  34→\n  35→/**\n  36→ * High-risk commands that require confirmation\n  37→ */\n  38→const HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'force-unlock']);\n  39→\n  40→/**\n  41→ * Internal config reference - can be overridden for testing\n  42→ * @type {Object}\n  43→ */\n  44→let _config = config;\n  45→\n  46→/**\n  47→ * Set config for testing purposes\n  48→ * @param {Object} testConfig\n  49→ */\n  50→export function setConfigForTesting(testConfig) {\n  51→  _config = testConfig;\n  52→}\n  53→\n  54→/**\n  55→ * Reset config to original (for testing cleanup)\n  56→ */\n  57→export function resetConfig() {\n  58→  _config = config;\n  59→}\n  60→\n  61→/**\n  62→ * Get user permission level\n  63→ * @param {string|number} userId - Telegram user ID\n  64→ * @returns {'admin'|'operator'|'viewer'}\n  65→ */\n  66→export function getUserRole(userId) {\n  67→  const userIdStr = String(userId);\n  68→  const configuredRole = _config.userPermissions.get(userIdStr);\n  69→\n  70→  if (configuredRole) {\n  71→    return configuredRole;\n  72→  }\n  73→\n  74→  // Default to operator for unknown users (AC-1.3)\n  75→  return 'operator';\n  76→}\n  77→\n  78→/**\n  79→ * Check if user is admin\n  80→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  81→ * @returns {boolean}\n  82→ */\n  83→export function isAdmin(userId) {\n  84→  return getUserRole(userId) === 'admin';\n  85→}\n  86→\n  87→/**\n  88→ * Check if user can execute command\n  89→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  90→ * @param {string} command - Command name\n  91→ * @returns {{ allowed: boolean, requiresConfirmation: boolean, reason?: string }}\n  92→ */\n  93→export function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n  94→  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n  95→  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n  96→\n  97→  // Special handling for exec command (AC-2.4, F-002)\n  98→  if (command === 'exec' && !_config.enableSystemExec) {\n  99→    return {\n 100→      allowed: false,\n 101→      requiresConfirmation: false,\n 102→      reason: '系统命令执行未启用。请在 .env 中设置 ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true。'\n 103→    };\n 104→  }\n 105→\n 106→  // Check role hierarchy\n 107→  const userLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[userRole];\n 108→  const requiredLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[minRole];\n 109→\n 110→  if (userLevel < requiredLevel) {\n 111→    return {\n 112→      allowed: false,\n 113→      requiresConfirmation: false,\n 114→      reason: `权限不足。此命令需要 ${minRole} 权限，当前权限: ${userRole}。`\n 115→    };\n 116→  }\n 117→\n 118→  // Check if this is a high-risk command requiring confirmation\n 119→  const requiresConfirmation = HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS.has(command);\n 120→\n 121→  return {\n 122→    allowed: true,\n 123→    requiresConfirmation\n 124→  };\n 125→}\n 126→\n 127→export default {\n 128→  getUserRole,\n 129→  checkCommandPermission,\n 130→  isAdmin,\n 131→  ROLE_HIERARCHY,\n 132→  setConfigForTesting,\n 133→  resetConfig\n 134→};\n 135→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:58:03.570Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"4464bc08-36d0-4b67-bccf-ef791824862e","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_82c3c3b2d32b457f9e21fe23","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Confirmation Manager Module\n   3→ * F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   4→ *\n   5→ * Manages confirmation flow for high-risk actions.\n   6→ * AC-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n   7→ */\n   8→\n   9→import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n  10→\n  11→/**\n  12→ * Default confirmation timeout (60 seconds per AC-4.3)\n  13→ */\n  14→const DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS = 60000;\n  15→\n  16→/**\n  17→ * Pending confirmations storage\n  18→ * Map<confirmId, ConfirmationEntry>\n  19→ */\n  20→const pendingConfirmations = new Map();\n  21→\n  22→/**\n  23→ * @typedef {Object} ConfirmationEntry\n  24→ * @property {string} confirmId\n  25→ * @property {string|number} userId\n  26→ * @property {string} action\n  27→ * @property {Object} params\n  28→ * @property {number} createdAt\n  29→ * @property {number} expiresAt\n  30→ */\n  31→\n  32→/**\n  33→ * Create pending confirmation\n  34→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  35→ * @param {string} action - Action name\n  36→ * @param {Object} params - Action parameters\n  37→ * @param {number} [timeoutMs=60000]\n  38→ * @returns {{ confirmId: string, message: string }}\n  39→ */\n  40→export function createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS) {\n  41→  const confirmId = randomUUID();\n  42→  const now = Date.now();\n  43→\n  44→  const entry = {\n  45→    confirmId,\n  46→    userId: String(userId),\n  47→    action,\n  48→    params,\n  49→    createdAt: now,\n  50→    expiresAt: now + timeoutMs\n  51→  };\n  52→\n  53→  pendingConfirmations.set(confirmId, entry);\n  54→\n  55→  const message = `⚠️ 确认执行操作: ${action}\\n参数: ${JSON.stringify(params)}\\n请在 60 秒内回复 CONFIRM 确认，或回复 CANCEL 取消。`;\n  56→\n  57→  return { confirmId, message };\n  58→}\n  59→\n  60→/**\n  61→ * Check confirmation status\n  62→ * @param {string} confirmId\n  63→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  64→ * @returns {{ status: 'pending'|'confirmed'|'expired'|'not_found', action?: string, params?: Object }}\n  65→ */\n  66→export function checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) {\n  67→  const entry = pendingConfirmations.get(confirmId);\n  68→\n  69→  if (!entry) {\n  70→    return { status: 'not_found' };\n  71→  }\n  72→\n  73→  // Verify userId matches\n  74→  if (entry.userId !== String(userId)) {\n  75→    return { status: 'not_found' };\n  76→  }\n  77→\n  78→  // Check if expired\n  79→  if (Date.now() > entry.expiresAt) {\n  80→    return { status: 'expired', action: entry.action, params: entry.params };\n  81→  }\n  82→\n  83→  return {\n  84→    status: 'pending',\n  85→    action: entry.action,\n  86→    params: entry.params\n  87→  };\n  88→}\n  89→\n  90→/**\n  91→ * Confirm pending action\n  92→ * @param {string} confirmId\n  93→ * @param {string|number} userId\n  94→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, action?: string, params?: Object, error?: string }}\n  95→ */\n  96→export function confirmAction(confirmId, userId) {\n  97→  const entry = pendingConfirmations.get(confirmId);\n  98→\n  99→  if (!entry) {\n 100→    return { ok: false, error: '确认请求不存在或已过期' };\n 101→  }\n 102→\n 103→  // Verify userId matches\n 104→  if (entry.userId !== String(userId)) {\n 105→    return { ok: false, error: '无权确认此操作' };\n 106→  }\n 107→\n 108→  // Check if expired\n 109→  if (Date.now() > entry.expiresAt) {\n 110→    return { ok: false, error: '确认请求已过期' };\n 111→  }\n 112→\n 113→  // Remove from pending (consumed)\n 114→  pendingConfirmations.delete(confirmId);\n 115→\n 116→  return {\n 117→    ok: true,\n 118→    action: entry.action,\n 119→    params: entry.params\n 120→  };\n 121→}\n 122→\n 123→/**\n 124→ * Cancel pending confirmation\n 125→ * @param {string} confirmId\n 126→ * @param {string|number} userId\n 127→ */\n 128→export function cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) {\n 129→  const entry = pendingConfirmations.get(confirmId);\n 130→\n 131→  if (!entry) {\n 132→    return;\n 133→  }\n 134→\n 135→  // Only allow creator to cancel\n 136→  if (entry.userId === String(userId)) {\n 137→    pendingConfirmations.delete(confirmId);\n 138→  }\n 139→}\n 140→\n 141→/**\n 142→ * Clear all expired confirmations\n 143→ * Should be called periodically\n 144→ */\n 145→export function clearExpiredConfirmations() {\n 146→  const now = Date.now();\n 147→\n 148→  for (const [confirmId, entry] of pendingConfirmations) {\n 149→    if (entry.expiresAt <= now) {\n 150→      pendingConfirmations.delete(confirmId);\n 151→    }\n 152→  }\n 153→}\n 154→\n 155→export default {\n 156→  createConfirmation,\n 157→  checkConfirmation,\n 158→  confirmAction,\n 159→  cancelConfirmation,\n 160→  clearExpiredConfirmations\n 161→};\n 162→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:58:03.570Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"1b043901-d9bb-45fa-aa7c-84dcc561241d","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9fcfe27b77694e94a86ef323","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Param Sanitizer Module\n   3→ * F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   4→ *\n   5→ * Provides parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection.\n   6→ */\n   7→\n   8→import path from 'node:path';\n   9→\n  10→/**\n  11→ * Dangerous patterns to detect\n  12→ * AC-3.1: Path traversal, absolute path escape, shell metacharacters\n  13→ * AC-3.3: Dangerous characters: ; | & $ ` ' \" ( ) < >\n  14→ */\n  15→const DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [\n  16→  { pattern: /\\.\\./, name: 'path traversal (..)' },\n  17→  { pattern: /[`$]/, name: 'shell injection ($ or `)' },\n  18→  { pattern: /~/, name: 'home directory (~)' },\n  19→  { pattern: /\\$\\(/, name: 'command substitution ($())' },\n  20→  { pattern: /\\|\\|/, name: 'command chain (||)' },\n  21→  { pattern: /&&/, name: 'command chain (&&)' },\n  22→  { pattern: /;/, name: 'command separator (;)' },\n  23→  { pattern: /\\|/, name: 'pipe (|)' },\n  24→  { pattern: /&/, name: 'ampersand (&)' },\n  25→  { pattern: /--exec\\b/, name: 'exec flag (--exec)' },\n  26→  { pattern: /--eval\\b/, name: 'eval flag (--eval)' },\n  27→  { pattern: /'/, name: 'single quote (\\')' },\n  28→  { pattern: /\"/, name: 'double quote (\")' },\n  29→  { pattern: /\\(/, name: 'left parenthesis ((' },\n  30→  { pattern: /\\)/, name: 'right parenthesis ())' },\n  31→  { pattern: /</, name: 'left angle bracket (<)' },\n  32→  { pattern: />/, name: 'right angle bracket (>)' }\n  33→];\n  34→\n  35→/**\n  36→ * TargetId valid format: [A-Za-z0-9_-]+\n  37→ */\n  38→const TARGET_ID_PATTERN = /^[A-Za-z0-9_-]+$/;\n  39→\n  40→/**\n  41→ * Check for dangerous patterns in input\n  42→ * @param {string} input\n  43→ * @returns {{ safe: boolean, patterns: string[] }}\n  44→ */\n  45→export function detectDangerousPatterns(input) {\n  46→  const detectedPatterns = [];\n  47→\n  48→  for (const { pattern, name } of DANGEROUS_PATTERNS) {\n  49→    if (pattern.test(input)) {\n  50→      detectedPatterns.push(name);\n  51→    }\n  52→  }\n  53→\n  54→  return {\n  55→    safe: detectedPatterns.length === 0,\n  56→    patterns: detectedPatterns\n  57→  };\n  58→}\n  59→\n  60→/**\n  61→ * Sanitize string parameter\n  62→ * @param {string} input - Raw input\n  63→ * @param {Object} options\n  64→ * @param {number} [options.maxLength=200]\n  65→ * @param {boolean} [options.isTargetId=false]\n  66→ * @param {boolean} [options.isPath=false]\n  67→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, value?: string, error?: string }}\n  68→ */\n  69→export function sanitizeParam(input, options = {}) {\n  70→  const { maxLength = 200, isTargetId = false, isPath = false } = options;\n  71→\n  72→  // Handle null/undefined\n  73→  if (input === null || input === undefined) {\n  74→    return { ok: false, error: '参数不能为空' };\n  75→  }\n  76→\n  77→  // Convert to string and trim\n  78→  const text = String(input).trim();\n  79→\n  80→  // Check for empty input\n  81→  if (!text) {\n  82→    return { ok: false, error: '参数不能为空' };\n  83→  }\n  84→\n  85→  // Check max length\n  86→  if (text.length > maxLength) {\n  87→    return { ok: false, error: `参数过长，最大 ${maxLength} 个字符` };\n  88→  }\n  89→\n  90→  // For targetId, check specific format (AC-3.2)\n  91→  if (isTargetId) {\n  92→    if (!TARGET_ID_PATTERN.test(text)) {\n  93→      return { ok: false, error: '目标 ID 格式无效，仅允许字母、数字、下划线和连字符' };\n  94→    }\n  95→    return { ok: true, value: text };\n  96→  }\n  97→\n  98→  // Check for dangerous patterns (AC-3.1, AC-3.3)\n  99→  const { safe, patterns } = detectDangerousPatterns(text);\n 100→  if (!safe) {\n 101→    // For isPath, allow certain patterns that are valid in paths\n 102→    if (isPath) {\n 103→      // Paths can have / and . but not .. or other dangerous patterns\n 104→      const pathSpecificPatterns = patterns.filter(\n 105→        (p) =>\n 106→          !p.includes('path traversal') ||\n 107→          // Only filter path traversal if it's actually .. (handled separately)\n 108→          false\n 109→      );\n 110→      if (pathSpecificPatterns.length > 0) {\n 111→        return { ok: false, error: `参数包含危险字符: ${pathSpecificPatterns.join(', ')}` };\n 112→      }\n 113→    } else {\n 114→      return { ok: false, error: `参数包含危险字符: ${patterns.join(', ')}` };\n 115→    }\n 116→  }\n 117→\n 118→  return { ok: true, value: text };\n 119→}\n 120→\n 121→/**\n 122→ * Validate path parameter\n 123→ * @param {string} inputPath - Path to validate\n 124→ * @param {string[]} allowedRoots - Allowed root directories\n 125→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, resolved?: string, error?: string }}\n 126→ */\n 127→export function validatePath(inputPath, allowedRoots) {\n 128→  // Handle null/undefined\n 129→  if (!inputPath) {\n 130→    return { ok: false, error: '路径不能为空' };\n 131→  }\n 132→\n 133→  const text = String(inputPath).trim();\n 134→  if (!text) {\n 135→    return { ok: false, error: '路径不能为空' };\n 136→  }\n 137→\n 138→  // Must be absolute path\n 139→  if (!path.isAbsolute(text)) {\n 140→    return { ok: false, error: '仅允许绝对路径' };\n 141→  }\n 142→\n 143→  // Check for path traversal\n 144→  if (text.includes('..')) {\n 145→    return { ok: false, error: '路径不允许包含 ..' };\n 146→  }\n 147→\n 148→  // Resolve to canonical path\n 149→  const resolved = path.resolve(text);\n 150→\n 151→  // Check against allowed roots\n 152→  if (allowedRoots && allowedRoots.length > 0) {\n 153→    const isWithinRoot = allowedRoots.some((root) => {\n 154→      const resolvedRoot = path.resolve(root);\n 155→      const relative = path.relative(resolvedRoot, resolved);\n 156→      return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n 157→    });\n 158→\n 159→    if (!isWithinRoot) {\n 160→      return { ok: false, error: '路径不在允许的根目录范围内' };\n 161→    }\n 162→  }\n 163→\n 164→  return { ok: true, resolved };\n 165→}\n 166→\n 167→export default {\n 168→  sanitizeParam,\n 169→  validatePath,\n 170→  detectDangerousPatterns\n 171→};\n 172→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:58:03.571Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"1a736074-4055-4ea1-9c24-10c37437733b","session_id":"62951781-27f6-43fd-92b7-2a78a8a15ac7","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_74c44fa2def54a28861828ae","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Audit Log Service\n   3→ *\n   4→ * F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - US-5: Audit Logging\n   5→ *\n   6→ * Handles writing and querying audit logs for sensitive operations.\n   7→ * Uses JSON Lines format for log entries with rotation support.\n   8→ *\n   9→ * Design Decisions:\n  10→ * - D3: JSON Lines format for easy parsing and append operations\n  11→ * - Async write to avoid blocking command execution\n  12→ * - Log rotation based on file size with configurable retention\n  13→ */\n  14→\n  15→import fs from 'node:fs';\n  16→import path from 'node:path';\n  17→import readline from 'node:readline';\n  18→import { once } from 'node:events';\n  19→\n  20→import { config } from '../config.js';\n  21→\n  22→/**\n  23→ * Default configuration\n  24→ */\n  25→const DEFAULT_CONFIG = {\n  26→  logPath: 'logs',\n  27→  maxSizeMb: 10,\n  28→  maxFiles: 5\n  29→};\n  30→\n  31→/**\n  32→ * Log file name\n  33→ */\n  34→const LOG_FILE_NAME = 'audit.log';\n  35→\n  36→/**\n  37→ * Internal state\n  38→ * @type {{ initialized: boolean, logPath: string, maxSizeBytes: number, maxFiles: number }}\n  39→ */\n  40→let _state = {\n  41→  initialized: false,\n  42→  logPath: DEFAULT_CONFIG.logPath,\n  43→  maxSizeBytes: DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxSizeMb * 1024 * 1024,\n  44→  maxFiles: DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxFiles\n  45→};\n  46→\n  47→/**\n  48→ * Reference to config for testing override\n  49→ */\n  50→let _config = config;\n  51→\n  52→/**\n  53→ * Set config for testing purposes\n  54→ * @param {Object} testConfig\n  55→ */\n  56→export function setConfigForTesting(testConfig) {\n  57→  _config = testConfig;\n  58→}\n  59→\n  60→/**\n  61→ * Reset config to original (for testing cleanup)\n  62→ */\n  63→export function resetConfig() {\n  64→  _config = config;\n  65→}\n  66→\n  67→/**\n  68→ * Initialize audit log service\n  69→ * @param {Object} options - Configuration options\n  70→ * @param {string} [options.logPath] - Log directory path (defaults to config.auditLogDir)\n  71→ * @param {number} [options.maxSizeMb] - Max size in MB before rotation (defaults to config.auditLogMaxSizeMb)\n  72→ * @param {number} [options.maxFiles] - Max rotated files to keep (defaults to config.auditLogMaxFiles)\n  73→ */\n  74→export function initAuditLogService(options = {}) {\n  75→  _state.logPath = options.logPath || _config.auditLogDir || DEFAULT_CONFIG.logPath;\n  76→  _state.maxSizeBytes = (options.maxSizeMb || _config.auditLogMaxSizeMb || DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxSizeMb) * 1024 * 1024;\n  77→  _state.maxFiles = options.maxFiles || _config.auditLogMaxFiles || DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxFiles;\n  78→\n  79→  // Create log directory if it doesn't exist\n  80→  if (!fs.existsSync(_state.logPath)) {\n  81→    fs.mkdirSync(_state.logPath, { recursive: true });\n  82→  }\n  83→\n  84→  _state.initialized = true;\n  85→}\n  86→\n  87→/**\n  88→ * Reset the audit log service state (for testing)\n  89→ */\n  90→export function resetAuditLogService() {\n  91→  _state = {\n  92→    initialized: false,\n  93→    logPath: DEFAULT_CONFIG.logPath,\n  94→    maxSizeBytes: DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxSizeMb * 1024 * 1024,\n  95→    maxFiles: DEFAULT_CONFIG.maxFiles\n  96→  };\n  97→}\n  98→\n  99→/**\n 100→ * Get the current log file path\n 101→ * @returns {string}\n 102→ */\n 103→function getLogFilePath() {\n 104→  return path.join(_state.logPath, LOG_FILE_NAME);\n 105→}\n 106→\n 107→/**\n 108→ * Check if log rotation is needed\n 109→ * @returns {boolean}\n 110→ */\n 111→function needsRotation() {\n 112→  const logFile = getLogFilePath();\n 113→  if (!fs.existsSync(logFile)) {\n 114→    return false;\n 115→  }\n 116→  const stats = fs.statSync(logFile);\n 117→  return stats.size >= _state.maxSizeBytes;\n 118→}\n 119→\n 120→/**\n 121→ * Perform log rotation\n 122→ * Rotates audit.log -> audit.log.1, audit.log.1 -> audit.log.2, etc.\n 123→ */\n 124→function rotateLog() {\n 125→  const logFile = getLogFilePath();\n 126→\n 127→  // Remove oldest file if at max files\n 128→  const oldestFile = `${logFile}.${_state.maxFiles}`;\n 129→  if (fs.existsSync(oldestFile)) {\n 130→    fs.unlinkSync(oldestFile);\n 131→  }\n 132→\n 133→  // Rotate existing files\n 134→  for (let i = _state.maxFiles - 1; i >= 1; i--) {\n 135→    const currentFile = `${logFile}.${i}`;\n 136→    const nextFile = `${logFile}.${i + 1}`;\n 137→    if (fs.existsSync(currentFile)) {\n 138→      fs.renameSync(currentFile, nextFile);\n 139→    }\n 140→  }\n 141→\n 142→  // Rotate current log to .1\n 143→  if (fs.existsSync(logFile)) {\n 144→    fs.renameSync(logFile, `${logFile}.1`);\n 145→  }\n 146→}\n 147→\n 148→/**\n 149→ * Log a sensitive action to the audit log\n 150→ * @param {Object} entry - Audit entry\n 151→ * @param {string|number} entry.userId - User ID\n 152→ * @param {string} [entry.role] - User role\n 153→ * @param {string} entry.action - Action name\n 154→ * @param {Object} [entry.params] - Action parameters\n 155→ * @param {string} entry.result - Result: 'success'|'denied'|'failed'\n 156→ * @param {string} [entry.reason] - Reason for denial/failure\n 157→ * @param {string} [entry.sessionId] - Session identifier\n 158→ * @returns {Promise<void>}\n 159→ */\n 160→export async function logAuditEntry(entry) {\n 161→  // Initialize with defaults if not already done\n 162→  if (!_state.initialized) {\n 163→    initAuditLogService();\n 164→  }\n 165→\n 166→  const logFile = getLogFilePath();\n 167→\n 168→  // Check for rotation before writing\n 169→  if (needsRotation()) {\n 170→    rotateLog();\n 171→  }\n 172→\n 173→  // Build log entry\n 174→  const logEntry = {\n 175→    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n 176→    userId: String(entry.userId),\n 177→    role: entry.role || 'unknown',\n 178→    action: entry.action,\n 179→    params: entry.params || {},\n 180→    result: entry.result,\n 181→    reason: entry.reason || null,\n 182→    sessionId: entry.sessionId || null\n 183→  };\n 184→\n 185→  // Write as JSON line\n 186→  const line = JSON.stringify(logEntry) + '\\n';\n 187→\n 188→  try {\n 189→    // Use appendFileSync for simplicity (async write could be added for performance)\n 190→    // For true async, we could use fs.promises.appendFile\n 191→    await fs.promises.appendFile(logFile, line, 'utf8');\n 192→  } catch (error) {\n 193→    // Log write failure should not block execution (NFR-2)\n 194→    console.error('[AuditLog] Failed to write audit entry:', error.message);\n 195→  }\n 196→}\n 197→\n 198→/**\n 199→ * Query audit logs with filters\n 200→ * @param {Object} filters - Query filters\n 201→ * @param {string|number} [filters.userId] - Filter by user ID\n 202→ * @param {string} [filters.action] - Filter by action name\n 203→ * @param {Date} [filters.startDate] - Filter entries after this date\n 204→ * @param {Date} [filters.endDate] - Filter entries before this date\n 205→ * @param {number} [filters.limit=100] - Maximum entries to return\n 206→ * @returns {Promise<Object[]>} Array of matching audit entries\n 207→ */\n 208→export async function queryAuditLogs(filters = {}) {\n 209→  // Initialize with defaults if not already done\n 210→  if (!_state.initialized) {\n 211→    initAuditLogService();\n 212→  }\n 213→\n 214→  const logFile = getLogFilePath();\n 215→\n 216→  if (!fs.existsSync(logFile)) {\n 217→    return [];\n 218→  }\n 219→\n 220→  const limit = filters.limit || 100;\n 221→  const userId = filters.userId != null ? String(filters.userId) : null;\n 222→  const action = filters.action || null;\n 223→  const startDate = filters.startDate ? new Date(filters.startDate) : null;\n 224→  const endDate = filters.endDate ? new Date(filters.endDate) : null;\n 225→\n 226→  const entries = [];\n 227→\n 228→  // Read log file(s) - start with current, then rotated files\n 229→  const filesToRead = [logFile];\n 230→\n 231→  // Add rotated files\n 232→  for (let i = 1; i <= _state.maxFiles; i++) {\n 233→    const rotatedFile = `${logFile}.${i}`;\n 234→    if (fs.existsSync(rotatedFile)) {\n 235→      filesToRead.push(rotatedFile);\n 236→    }\n 237→  }\n 238→\n 239→  // Read and parse entries\n 240→  for (const file of filesToRead) {\n 241→    try {\n 242→      const content = await fs.promises.readFile(file, 'utf8');\n 243→      const lines = content.trim().split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n 244→\n 245→      for (const line of lines) {\n 246→        try {\n 247→          const entry = JSON.parse(line);\n 248→\n 249→          // Apply filters\n 250→          if (userId && String(entry.userId) !== userId) continue;\n 251→          if (action && entry.action !== action) continue;\n 252→\n 253→          if (startDate || endDate) {\n 254→            const entryDate = new Date(entry.timestamp);\n 255→            if (startDate && entryDate < startDate) continue;\n 256→            if (endDate && entryDate > endDate) continue;\n 257→          }\n 258→\n 259→          entries.push(entry);\n 260→        } catch {\n 261→          // Skip malformed entries (corrupted lines)\n 262→          continue;\n 263→        }\n 264→      }\n 265→    } catch {\n 266→      // Skip files that can't be read\n 267→      continue;\n 268→    }\n 269→  }\n 270→\n 271→  // Sort by timestamp descending (most recent first)\n 272→  entries.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.timestamp) - new Date(a.timestamp));\n 273→\n 274→  // Apply limit\n 275→  return entries.slice(0, limit);\n 276→}\n 277→\n 278→/**\n 279→ * Get audit log statistics\n 280→ * @returns {Promise<{ totalEntries: number, fileSize: number, oldestEntry: Date | null }>}\n 281→ */\n 282→export async function getAuditLogStats() {\n 283→  // Initialize with defaults if not already done\n 284→  if (!_state.initialized) {\n 285→    initAuditLogService();\n 286→  }\n 287→\n 288→  const logFile = getLogFilePath();\n 289→  let totalEntries = 0;\n 290→  let fileSize = 0;\n 291→  let oldestEntry = null;\n 292→\n 293→  if (fs.existsSync(logFile)) {\n 294→    const stats = fs.statSync(logFile);\n 295→    fileSize = stats.size;\n 296→\n 297→    try {\n 298→      const content = await fs.promises.readFile(logFile, 'utf8');\n 299→      const lines = content.trim().split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n 300→      totalEntries = lines.length;\n 301→\n 302→      // Find oldest entry (first line in file)\n 303→      if (lines.length > 0) {\n 304→        try {\n 305→          const firstEntry = JSON.parse(lines[0]);\n 306→          oldestEntry = new Date(firstEntry.timestamp);\n 307→        } catch {\n 308→          // Ignore parse errors\n 309→        }\n 310→      }\n 311→    } catch {\n 312→      // Ignore read errors\n 313→    }\n 314→  }\n 315→\n 316→  return {\n 317→    totalEntries,\n 318→    fileSize,\n 319→    oldestEntry\n 320→  };\n 321→}\n 322→\n 323→export default {\n 324→  initAuditLogService,\n 325→  logAuditEntry,\n 326→  queryAuditLogs,\n 327→  resetAuditLogService,\n 328→  getAuditLogStats,\n 329→  setConfigForTesting,\n 330→  resetConfig\n 331→};\n 332→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdeb0eca880b82916352a46acc4a0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:58:03.571Z","_requestId":"9a060372b45d4f5a90dab23b747027c6"}
