pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  29→\n  30→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  31→\n  32→- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  33→- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  34→- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  35→- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  36→\n  37→### Verification\n  38→\n  39→- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  40→- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  41→- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  42→\n  43→---\n  44→\n  45→## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  46→\n  47→**Status:** completed  \n  48→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  49→\n  50→### Deliverables\n  51→\n  52→- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  53→- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  54→- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  55→- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  56→- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  57→- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  58→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  59→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  60→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  61→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  62→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  63→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  64→- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  65→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  66→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  67→\n  68→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  69→\n  70→- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  71→- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  72→- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  73→- US-4: Logs query with file