atus command showing version info and content summary\n 119→- US-5: Plan Integrity Protection - Validation precedes save, current version preserved on error\n 120→- US-6: Pipeline Integration - resolvePlanListPath() for dynamic plan path resolution\n 121→\n 122→### Commands Implemented\n 123→\n 124→| Command | Subcommands | Description |\n 125→|---------|-------------|-------------|\n 126→| `/plan` | status, versions, use, rollback, validate | Manage plan files |\n 127→\n 128→### Verification\n 129→\n 130→- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 131→- All 18 tasks completed\n 132→- Unit tests: 19 passing\n 133→- Integration tests: 10 passing\n 134→\n 135→---\n 136→\n 137→## F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n 138→\n 139→**Status:** completed\n 140→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 141→\n 142→### Deliverables\n 143→\n 144→- `src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js` - File-based lock management with PID validation\n 145→- `src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js` - State file reading/writing for daemon and pipeline state\n 146→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 6 new error codes for F-004\n 147→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Extended with lock/state path resolvers\n 148→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Unified pipeline control API with concurrency protection\n 149→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 150→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 151→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 152→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 153→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` and `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js`\n 154→- Unit tests in `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js`\n 155→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 156→\n 157→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 158→\n 159→- US-1: Unified Pipeline Start - startPipeline with daemon/foreground modes, lock acquisition\n 160→- US-2: Pipeline Stop - stopPipeline with ALREADY_STOPPED handling, lock release\n 161→- US-3: Target Retry - retryTarget with validation and mode support\n 162→- US-4: Run Single Feature - runSingle without lock (independent execution)\n 163→- US-5: Status Query - getStatus with daemon/pipeline state, lastResult\n 164→- US-6: Logs Query - getLogs with line limit, missing file handling\n 165→- US-7: Concurrency Protection - lock-manager with stale lock cleanup, forceUnlock\n 166→- US-8: Error Mapping - Consistent error codes with hint/context fields\n 167→- US-9: Telegram Handler Integration - All handlers updated to use pipeline-controller\n 168→\n 169→### Error Codes Added\n 170→\n 171→| Code | Description |\n 172→|------|-------------|\n 173→| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | Pipeline already running |\n 174→| ALREADY_STOPPED | Pipeline not running |\n 175→| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | No active pipeline |\n 176→| INVALID_TARGET | Missing or invalid target ID |\n 177→| TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE | Target state not retryable |\n 178→| DAEMON_START_FAILED | Failed to start daemon |\n 179→\n 180→### Key Decisions\n 181→\n 182→- D1: File lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (no external dependencies)\n 183→- D2: Separate lock-manager module for single responsibility\n 184→- D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n 185→- D4: New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service\n 186→- D5: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 187→\n 188→### Verification\n 189→\n 190→- Code review: PASS\n 191→- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 192→- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n 193→- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n 194→\n 195→---\n 196→\n 197→## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n 198→\n 199→**Status:** completed\n 200→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n 201→\n 202→### Deliverables\n 203→\n 204→- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n 205→- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n 206→- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n 207→- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n 208→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n 209→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n 210→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n 211→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n 212→- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n 213→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n 214→\n 215→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 216→\n 217→- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n 218→- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n 219→- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n 220→- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n 221→- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n 222→- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n 223→\n 224→### Commands Enhanced\n 225→\n 226→| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n 227→|---------|----------------|-------------|\n 228→| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n 229→| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n 230→\n 231→### Error Codes Added\n 232→\n 233→| Code | Description |\n 234→|------|-------------|\n 235→| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n 236→| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n 237→| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n 238→| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n 239→| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n 240→| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n 241→| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n 242→| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n 243→\n 244→### Key Decisions\n 245→\n 246→- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n 247→- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n 248→- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n 249→- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n 250→- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n 251→- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n 252→- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s)\n 253→\n 254→### Verification\n 255→\n 256→- All 77 tasks completed\n 257→- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n 258→- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n 259→- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n 260→- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n 261→- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%\n 262→\n 263→---\n 264→\n 265→## F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 266→\n 267→**Status:** completed\n 268→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 269→\n 270→### Deliverables\n 271→\n 272→- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer) with env config\n 273→- `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` - Parameter sanitization with path traversal and shell injection protection\n 274→- `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` - Text-based confirmation flow with 60s timeout\n 275→- `src/security/guard.js` - Unified guard middleware for command handlers\n 276→- `src/security/system-guard.js` - System exec command guard with ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC control\n 277→- `src/security/index.js` - Module exports\n 278→- `src/services/audit-log-service.js` - JSON Lines audit logging with rotation (10MB/5 files)\n 279→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js` - /audit command for log query (admin-only)\n 280→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated with force-unlock, confirmation flow, audit logging\n 281→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated with confirmation flow\n 282→- `src/config.js` - Extended with security configuration\n 283→- `.env.example` - Updated with USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_* vars\n 284→- Unit tests in `tests/security/`\n 285→- Unit tests in `tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js`\n 286→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js`, `tests/integration/security-extended.test.js`\n 287→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm`\n 288→\n 289→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 290→\n 291→- US-1: User Permission Levels - Three-tier model (admin/operator/viewer) with USER_PERMISSIONS env config\n 292→- US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization - stop/reset/force-unlock require admin, retry requires operator\n 293→- US-3: Parameter Sanitization - Path traversal, shell injection, and dangerous character protection\n 294→- US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions - Text-based CONFIRM with 60s timeout, --force for admin\n 295→- US-5: Audit Logging - JSON Lines format with rotation, query by user/time/action\n 296→\n 297→### High-Risk Command Matrix\n 298→\n 299→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation |\n 300→|---------|---------------|--------------|\n 301→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 302→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 303→| `retry` | operator | No |\n 304→| `exec` | admin | No (ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC) |\n 305→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 306→\n 307→### Key Decisions\n 308→\n 309→- D1: Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer)\n 310→- D2: Text-based confirmation (\"CONFIRM\") instead of inline keyboard\n 311→- D3: JSON Lines audit log format with rotation\n 312→- D4: --force flag only for admin users\n 313→\n 314→### Verification\n 315→\n 316→- Code re